Reply.create!([
  { post_id: 1, user_id: 2, content: "Bella did not expect Forks High to be a linoleum-lined Fight Club, but she's on her way to her second class of the day and, lo and behold, a boy <em>deliberately assaults</em> one who's about half again his size.  And then it turns into a massacre - an entirely predictable massacre.  The smaller kid's martial arts teachers have failed him.  If they even exist.<br><br>Bella turns to the boy who's shepherding her between classes; he's standing among the rubberneckers.  \"Why isn't anyone getting a teacher?  Not to mention the nurse?\"  And, in a lower voice, \"Is this <em>common</em>?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 102, created_at: "2012-09-13 05:14:00", reply_order: 0 },
  { post_id: 1, user_id: 3, content: "The predictable massacre continues. The boy getting massacred is grinning like it's his birthday and someone just got him a pony, or possibly a stripper. This only seems to annoy his victim/assailant even more.<br><br>\"That's Delaney Hammond,\" Eric whispers back, \"with the curly hair and the getting beat up. He moved here last year. Nobody knows what's up with him, but he does this all the time. I heard he went to the hospital in November or something.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-09-13 05:22:00", reply_order: 1 },
  { post_id: 1, user_id: 2, content: "And he's still among the general population.  Grand.  She wonders if Charlie knows.  \"Does he do 'this' to everyone, or just people who eat my weight in protein powder for breakfast?  Not that he's not obviously getting the worse end of things, now, but if he just pushes people into sharp corners at random...\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-13 05:24:00", reply_order: 2 },
  { post_id: 1, user_id: 3, content: "\"...He's never done it to <em>me</em>,\" Eric offers.<br><br>Eric definitely does not eat Bella's weight in protein powder for breakfast.<br><br>\"And I've never seen him, you know, beating somebody <em>else</em> up.\"<br><br>On the floor, Delaney has graduated from grinning to high-pitched wheezing giggles, and the boy hitting him is exhibiting increasing disgust.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-09-13 05:27:00", reply_order: 3 },
  { post_id: 1, user_id: 2, content: "Bella decides that she's going to inform a teacher, and Charlie, anyway, because she has <em>heard</em> of the bystander effect.  She also decides that she's just going to have to be late to class in case she's the only person in the hallway with the presence of mind to make sure the idiot doesn't drown in his own blood or choke on a tooth or something.  She produces a pocket-size notebook and writes down <em>screw the first rule of Fight Club</em>.  \"I'm going to stay here in case he needs an emergency vehicle,\" she tells Eric.  \"I'm one of, like, two people in town who can get ahold of one <em>faster</em> than the 911 dispatcher.  Can you repeat the directions to building four again?  I don't want to keep you.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-13 05:32:00", reply_order: 4 },
  { post_id: 1, user_id: 3, content: "Eric obligingly recites the appropriate directions, although he keeps getting distracted by the ongoing spectacle.<br><br>The ongoing spectacle... goes on. The boy on top is slowing down, though, issuing more scowls than punches.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-09-13 05:37:00", reply_order: 5 },
  { post_id: 1, user_id: 2, content: "\"Excuse me,\" calls Bella.  Because everyone knows who she is - whose daughter she is - so far, that might be enough.  She poises her pen over her notebook.  \"Punching person.  Can I have your name?  First and last, please?\"<br><br>Because she doesn't really <em>want</em> to be late to class.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 105, created_at: "2012-09-13 05:38:00", reply_order: 6 },
  { post_id: 1, user_id: 3, content: "Punching Person pauses his punching and looks up at her, confused.<br><br>\"What the hell do you want?\" he asks, despite the fact that she has made it pretty obvious.<br><br>Delaney tilts his head back to look at her and grins, displaying bloody teeth. \"Get in line, sister,\" he says in a lazy Brooklyn accent, \"I'm not done.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-09-13 05:41:00", reply_order: 7 },
  { post_id: 1, user_id: 2, content: "Bella ignores the instigator-slash-victim, although she takes it as reassurance on the subject of his health that he is capable of speech.  \"Your name,\" she says.  And apparently it wasn't enough, so, she adds, \"Like so: I'm  Bella Swan.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-13 05:43:00", reply_order: 8 },
  { post_id: 1, user_id: 3, content: "\"...Dave,\" says Punching Person. He looks down at Delaney, frowns, and then gets up, shaking out his right hand; it's looking bloody around the knuckles.<br><br>Delaney stretches out on the floor like it's a nice comfy bed, rolls over, and hauls himself to his feet, opening and closing his jaw as though testing that it retains full functionality. \"Thanks for the workout,\" he tosses over his shoulder as he walks away. \"Call me.\"<br><br>\"Freak,\" mutters apparently-Dave. Delaney stops in his tracks, clenching his jaw and tensing his arms and shoulders.<br><br>Then he relaxes and keeps going like nothing happened. The crowd begins to disperse.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-13 05:50:00", reply_order: 9 },
  { post_id: 1, user_id: 2, content: "\"Do <em>you</em> know his last name?\" Bella asks Eric, exasperated, as she lets the traffic pull her along with him to her next class.  She's had various aspects of what makes witnesses annoying inculcated into her head from a young age, and knowing only the name \"Dave\" would be one of them.<br><br>She also writes, <em>Delaney dislikes word 'freak'.  Word does not appear to have provoked push into locker (?)</em>", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-13 05:53:00", reply_order: 10 },
  { post_id: 1, user_id: 3, content: "\"Sure,\" says the ever-helpful Eric. \"That's David Farber.\"<br><br>If there is anything else he knows about David Farber, he is not volunteering it.<br><br>(Delaney turns a corner in front of them; the sound of his cheerful humming recedes into the distance.)", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-13 05:58:00", reply_order: 11 },
  { post_id: 1, user_id: 2, content: "<em>David Farber.  Felony assault?  (Does provocation invalidate that?)</em> Bella writes.  \"Thanks,\" she says, and she moves on to class.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 43, created_at: "2012-09-13 06:00:00", reply_order: 12 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 3, content: "He arrives very shortly after she does, pauses by the supply of basketballs for a moment, and then wanders over her way instead.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 00:58:00", reply_order: 0 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 2, content: "\"Good afternoon,\" she says.  \"How did you break your ribs?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-14 00:59:00", reply_order: 1 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 3, content: "\"...Well hi to you too,\" he says, amused, and plops onto the floor next to her mat. \"What do you care?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-09-14 01:01:00", reply_order: 2 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 2, content: "\"Because I don't know the answer,\" Bella says, working a cramp out of her hand acquired via notetaking.  \"And it doesn't fit what else I know, oddly enough.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 43, created_at: "2012-09-14 01:02:00", reply_order: 3 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 3, content: "\"Annnnd what if I say I promised I wouldn't tell?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-09-14 01:05:00", reply_order: 4 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 2, content: "Bella moves into a butterfly stretch.  \"I'd start wondering who you'd promise that to - and why.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-14 01:07:00", reply_order: 5 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 3, content: "\"Maybe they asked r<em>eee</em>ally nicely,\" he suggests, distorting the word to at least three times its normal length and adding a wink to make his intended meaning more clear.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-09-14 01:15:00", reply_order: 6 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 2, content: "\"That's one hypothesis I could consider,\" Bella agrees brightly.  \"And keep or discard, according to evidence.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-14 01:16:00", reply_order: 7 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 3, content: "\"Knock yourself out,\" he says, amused. \"You sure do like knowing stuff, don'tcha.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 01:25:00", reply_order: 8 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 2, content: "\"It compares <em>exceedingly</em> favorably to the alternative.  Would you like to hear my speculations so far?\" says Bella, still smiling.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-14 01:26:00", reply_order: 9 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 3, content: "He shrugs. \"Sure, why not.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-09-14 01:27:00", reply_order: 10 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 2, content: "Bella's smile turns into a thinner smirk.  \"When you get beat up at school, that's not a secret.  If Dave Farber had broken your ribs and my father decided this was a crime he needed to prosecute, he could have gotten twenty people to tell him exactly who did it without any help from you at all.  So it wasn't a student.  Probably not a teacher either, especially since teachers beating up students isn't commonly a thing.  You didn't arrive at the hospital in an ambulance, but as a passenger in a car your family owns.  So you were not in the middle of nowhere when injured, and you were not unescorted - or you had access to a phone and you could get at it while you had your ribs broken, which is less likely.  It's possible the driver did it, but you've had the same one since that time, and I'd expect an incident like that to cause staff turnover, wouldn't you?  And you know what, I doubt your family makes a lot of family trips to places where you can get into fights.  And your driver wouldn't say where you came from even when a cop demanded the information.  Did someone ask the driver <em>reaaaally</em> nicely too?  But <em>I</em> think it happened at home.\"<br><br>She pauses, and tilts her head, stretching her arms, looking more severe.  \"You know what sort of beating-up relationship <em>is</em> commonly a thing?\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-14 01:40:00", reply_order: 11 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 3, content: "\"Is it the kind you can buy and have delivered?\" he asks, innocently.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-09-14 01:42:00", reply_order: 12 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 2, content: "\"Nope.  Typically acquired as an inheritance.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-14 01:42:00", reply_order: 13 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 3, content: "\"Oooh, now <em>that's</em> kinky.\" He laughs. \"Nope. Nice try, though.\" Generously, \"I didn't pay anybody for it, either.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-09-14 01:45:00", reply_order: 14 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 2, content: "\"I do think you are clever enough to avoid the problem of conspicuously saying 'no, no, no, plead the fifth, no',\" Bella says.  \"If you aren't going to produce a competing explanation, your denials are the whistling of the wind.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-14 01:47:00", reply_order: 15 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 3, content: "He shakes his head. \"Sorry, babe,\" he says, \"you're not gettin' the story out of me <em>that</em> easy.\" Brightly, \"But cheer up! Now if I piss you off you've got a great way to make my life hell for a while!\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 01:51:00", reply_order: 16 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 2, content: "\"Not that easily, hm?  I suppose I could always try asking nicely, if no other information presents itself; I got this far in about a day.\"  She smiles.  \"Are you likely to piss me off?\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-14 01:53:00", reply_order: 17 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 3, content: "\"Not on purpose,\" he assures her.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 01:55:00", reply_order: 18 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 2, content: "\"Oh?  You do both kinds of pissing people off, then?  I suppose there'd be no point to deliberately annoying someone who demonstrably,\" she gestures at the mat, \"cannot beat you up.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-14 01:56:00", reply_order: 19 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 3, content: "\"If you could beat me up, I'd <em>ask</em>,\" he says. \"Nicely, even.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-09-14 01:58:00", reply_order: 20 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 2, content: "\"Even if all you did was lie there I would wind up kicking myself in the nose or something embarrassing like that, and that would be if I <em>wished</em> to beat you up.  Not all aversion to violence is self-preservation <em>or</em> concern for the wishes of the...\"  She mulls over word choice, decides there isn't a better term ready to hand.  \"Victim.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-14 01:59:00", reply_order: 21 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 3, content: "He shrugs. \"And look at me, not asking.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 02:00:00", reply_order: 22 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 2, content: "\"Mm.\"  She changes the subject.  \"My dad knows your housekeeper.  Hilary.  They're friends.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-14 02:02:00", reply_order: 23 },
  { post_id: 3, user_id: 3, content: "\"Huh,\" he says. \"Didn't know that.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 02:06:00", reply_order: 24 },
  { post_id: 4, user_id: 2, content: "Bella brought her lunch today and is already sitting down, waiting for Jessica or Angela or Eric or someone to appear and sit with her.  Oh look.  A distraction.  This is probably going to be the most visually arresting thing in the room presently anyway; she directs her attention away from the door and towards Delaney and the person who does not like him for probably perfectly good reasons.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-14 02:27:00", reply_order: 0 },
  { post_id: 4, user_id: 3, content: "The other boy, who apparently dislikes being ignored, grabs Delaney's arm as he picks up his tray.<br><br>\"Not today, honeybunch,\" Delaney says mildly.<br><br>\"Faggot,\" his pursuer sneers, letting go with a shove that sends Delaney stumbling forward.<br><br>He just laughs, unperturbed. \"Why, you want some? Fifty bucks,\" he offers. \"A hundred and I'll do it right here.\"<br><br>That was not in the script. The other boy frowns as he processes the meaning of the words, and then his head jerks back in outraged surprise. \"Freak!\" he spits.<br><br>And all of a sudden there is a shower of food, plates, and cutlery and Delaney's tray is smacking him across the face.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 02:35:00", reply_order: 1 },
  { post_id: 4, user_id: 2, content: "Bella takes out her notebook and draws a plus sign next to a certain line.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 102, created_at: "2012-09-14 02:37:00", reply_order: 2 },
  { post_id: 4, user_id: 3, content: "Predictably, there is a fight.<br><br>This time, though, Delaney is really <em>in</em> it instead of just laughing as he gets pounded into the floor.<br><br>It makes a considerable difference.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 02:38:00", reply_order: 3 },
  { post_id: 4, user_id: 2, content: "Why aren't the cafeteria ladies doing anything?  They're <em>right there</em>.  They are <em>right there</em>.<br><br>Bella gets out her phone.  She dials Charlie's number, but doesn't hit send yet.  \"Delaney!\" she hollers.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-14 02:40:00", reply_order: 4 },
  { post_id: 4, user_id: 3, content: "He doesn't react even slightly. Like he doesn't hear her, or like he doesn't care, it's hard to tell.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 02:43:00", reply_order: 5 },
  { post_id: 4, user_id: 2, content: "Bella doesn't call her dad, yet, but she does march around the altercation to address the cafeteria ladies.  \"If you are not equipped to intervene,\" she says, \"you need to get someone who is.  Try Ms. Finch if you don't have a better idea.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 105, created_at: "2012-09-14 02:45:00", reply_order: 6 },
  { post_id: 4, user_id: 3, content: "The cafeteria ladies look at each other, then at the brawling boys. By some unspoken consensus, one of them turns and disappears through the door behind the counter.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-14 02:49:00", reply_order: 7 },
  { post_id: 4, user_id: 2, content: "In the meantime, there is still a fight.  \"DELANEY!\" shouts Bella.  Is she the only person in the room who doesn't see the status quo of \"Delaney periodically gets into injurious physical altercations with classmates\" as an okay thing?", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-14 02:51:00", reply_order: 8 },
  { post_id: 4, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yeah, what?\" he yells back, ducking under a punch.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 02:53:00", reply_order: 9 },
  { post_id: 4, user_id: 2, content: "\"The cafeteria lady is getting Ms. Finch or someone.  You might want to consider disengaging before she gets back.  Other Guy, you too.  Perhaps Delaney should go stand in that corner and you in the opposite one and you can glare at each other, does that sound good?  Other Guy can rest assured that Delaney will get the crap beaten out of him one way or another within the next twenty-four hours.  Delaney can meditate on overreactions and write a monograph on them later.  Okay?\"  She has to pause here and there to be heard over the sound of fighting.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-14 02:56:00", reply_order: 10 },
  { post_id: 4, user_id: 3, content: "...Delaney starts laughing.<br><br>The other guy shoots Bella an incredulous glance, of which Delaney does not take immediate advantage with violence.<br><br>This leaves them not fighting anymore, and it is not a state they seem inclined to resume.<br><br><br><br>From the door comes the sound of slow, measured applause.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:00:00", reply_order: 11 },
  { post_id: 4, user_id: 2, content: "Bella regains her calm slowly, and mostly by the mechanism of adjusting her hair, before looking to the source of the clapping.  \"Hello, Ms. Finch,\" she says, relieved.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:02:00", reply_order: 12 },
  { post_id: 4, user_id: 3, content: "\"So I don't have to put anybody in a detention he's not gonna show up for anyway,\" says Ms. Finch, giving Bella a nod.<br><br>\"Nope,\" says Delaney, very cheerfully.<br><br>\"Congratulations,\" she deadpans.<br><br>Delaney tips his head Bellaward. \"Blame her.\"<br><br>The other kid, what with the inhibiting presence of a teacher, shuffles slowly away.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:06:00", reply_order: 13 },
  { post_id: 4, user_id: 2, content: "Bella inhales deeply, exhales, and smiles politely at Ms. Finch.  \"Thanks for appearing so quickly.  It was not guaranteed that I'd be able to say anything useful.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:08:00", reply_order: 14 },
  { post_id: 4, user_id: 3, content: "\"No problem,\" says Ms. Finch.<br><br>Delaney picks up the single intact item out of the remains of his lunch - a bottle of juice - opens it, and heads for the door. People get out of his way with remarkable speed, except for Ms. Finch, who stays put.<br><br>\"Any chance you'll help clean that up?\" she asks him.<br><br>...He pauses to consider this question.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:12:00", reply_order: 15 },
  { post_id: 4, user_id: 2, content: "Bella is reasonably sure that <em>she</em> is not responsible for cleanup.  She sits back down in her seat and eats her little package of popcorn.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 43, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:14:00", reply_order: 16 },
  { post_id: 4, user_id: 3, content: "\"Nah,\" says Delaney. Ms. Finch doesn't argue, just steps aside to let him leave the room. The lunch lady who went after her reappears, and the normal course of lunch resumes, plus an expected buzz of gossip and the minor kerfuffle of Ms. Finch cornering the other boy and getting a promise of cleanup out of <em>him</em>, which she remains for a few minutes to supervise.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:17:00", reply_order: 17 },
  { post_id: 4, user_id: 2, content: "Bella has eaten three kernels of popcorn before Jessica finishes her own lunch transaction, plops into the seat at Bella's left, and demands a word-for-word recap.<br><br>Bella sighs very quietly and provides.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 43, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:20:00", reply_order: 18 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 3, content: "Delaney is sitting on a parking block at the very corner of the parking lot, about twenty feet from Bella's car, under a tree. When he spots her, he waves.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:30:00", reply_order: 0 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 2, content: "Bella waves back.<br><br>That's all a wave calls for, really.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:31:00", reply_order: 1 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 3, content: "When she's closer to her car, he calls, \"Yours?\" and gestures to indicate it.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:32:00", reply_order: 2 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 2, content: "\"Yeah, move-in present,\" she acknowledges, patting the car.  She unlocks the driver's side door.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:33:00", reply_order: 3 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 3, content: "\"Lucky you.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:34:00", reply_order: 4 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 2, content: "\"Yep.\"  This appears to be turning into a conversation.  \"I expected to have to get rides in the police cruiser until I could find a carpool.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:36:00", reply_order: 5 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 3, content: "\"...Rides in the police cruiser,\" he repeats, raising his eyebrows.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:38:00", reply_order: 6 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 2, content: "\"He doesn't have another car,\" she says.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:43:00", reply_order: 7 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yeah, I missed the part where your dad's a cop,\" says Delaney. \"Huh. You really <em>could</em> ruin my life.\"<br><br>He sounds oddly appreciative of this fact.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:44:00", reply_order: 8 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 2, content: "\"I was getting the impression I didn't have to say anything beyond possibly my last name,\" says Bella.  \"Small town, and everything; people keep picking up on it without being told.  He's the chief of police.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:45:00", reply_order: 9 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 3, content: "\"I didn't really catch your name,\" he admits. \"Or his, if I've even met him, I dunno. Or much of anybody's except Finch.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:48:00", reply_order: 10 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 2, content: "\"I <em>said</em> my name, in front of you,\" she says.  \"The other day, when I had to explain to Dave how telling people one's name works.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:49:00", reply_order: 11 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yep,\" he agrees, \"you did. Then I forgot it.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:50:00", reply_order: 12 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 2, content: "\"It's Bella Swan,\" she says.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:51:00", reply_order: 13 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 3, content: "\"Hi,\" he says amicably. \"Nice to meetcha. Don't call me Delaney.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:51:00", reply_order: 14 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 2, content: "\"What should I call you?  Jessica was only able to produce one of your middle names but assures me there are two.  There's 'Hammond'.  Or 'Junior',\" Bella says amiably.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:53:00", reply_order: 15 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 3, content: "He makes an eloquent face at 'Junior'.<br><br>\"Which one'd she come up with?\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:54:00", reply_order: 16 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 2, content: "\"The one she knows is 'Kermit'.  I'm not entirely sure if she has been pranked or not, with that one.  And haven't gone to the office to inquire.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:55:00", reply_order: 17 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 3, content: "\"Nope, she's on the level. Delaney Kermit Erskine Hammond,\" he recites. \"I hate the whole fucking thing. Well, Kermit's kind of hilarious.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:56:00", reply_order: 18 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 2, content: "\"You still haven't told me what you'd rather be called, Kermit.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:57:00", reply_order: 19 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 3, content: "He mulls this over for a few seconds, grinning.<br><br>Then he says, definitively: \"Alice.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-09-14 03:59:00", reply_order: 20 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 2, content: "\"Alice.  You realize if I call you that - for instance, at the top of my lungs trying to keep you from cracking someone's jaw - no one will have any idea who I'm talking to and I will appear to be a maniac.  Perhaps you could wear a nametag.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-14 04:01:00", reply_order: 21 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 3, content: "\"<em>I'll</em> know who you're talking to,\" he points out. \"If anybody gives you shit, I'll back you up. Maybe I'll start wearing those little blue dresses.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 04:03:00", reply_order: 22 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 2, content: "\"I'm not actually sure I could bring myself to yell 'Alice' when referring to you in the first place.  It's pretty hard to scream in a crowded room at all, and the difficulty increases when what one wishes to scream will predictably seem strange to the audience.  Maybe I'll just call you Alice when talking at a normal volume, like this, and I'll call you 'belligerent idiot' if I have to break up another fight.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-14 04:06:00", reply_order: 23 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 3, content: "\"Works for me,\" he says cheerfully.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 04:07:00", reply_order: 24 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 2, content: "\"Well,\" she says.  \"Now we know each other's names.  And nicknames.  See you around, Alice.\"  She mocks a salute, and hops into her car.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-14 04:08:00", reply_order: 25 },
  { post_id: 5, user_id: 3, content: "He waves cheerfully to her as she drives away.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 04:10:00", reply_order: 26 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 3, content: "<br><br><br><br>There is no longer an empty chair to her left.<br><br>\"Hi, Bella,\" says Alice as he deposits his tray on the table. His lunch is almost entirely cafeteria-sourced, with the exception of a mysterious opaque Tupperware container.<br><br>He bears no more visible injuries than he did yesterday, nor does he have the stiffness of movement that might indicate extensive non-visible injuries.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-09-16 02:39:00", reply_order: 0 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 2, content: "\"Hullo,\" returns Bella.  \"Have you met Angela, Jessica, and Mike?\"<br><br>Angela, Jessica, and Mike are nonplussed.<br><br>\"Also,\" says Bella, \"more to the point, does that container by any chance serve as a container for cake?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-16 02:41:00", reply_order: 1 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 3, content: "\"Got it in one,\" he says cheerfully. \"Hi everybody. I have no clue who any of you are.\" He opens the container and slides it towards Bella; two slices of cake rest within. \"Want one? Compliments of you know who.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-09-16 02:48:00", reply_order: 2 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 2, content: "\"I want both, but I won't secretly resent you forever if you give me exactly one,\" Bella says, helping herself to a slice.  \"They are Angela,\" she points, \"and Jessica, and Mike.\"<br><br>\"Hello,\" says Jessica gamely.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-16 02:49:00", reply_order: 3 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 3, content: "\"Nice to meetcha.\" He waves his fork vaguely at the three strangers and then pounces on his lunch, exhibiting absolutely none of the table manners he did last night.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-16 02:52:00", reply_order: 4 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 2, content: "Bella finishes her pasta-item, bites her apple and determines it to be an inferior specimen of applehood, and then devours her cake.<br><br>\"I didn't know you were friends with Hammond,\" says Mike.<br><br>Bella's mouth is full of cake.  If Alice wants his nomenclature corrected he might have to do it himself.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-16 02:54:00", reply_order: 5 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 3, content: "\"That's 'cause it only happened last night,\" Alice volunteers between noms.<br><br>...While technically true, this is perhaps a tiny bit misleading.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-09-16 02:56:00", reply_order: 6 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 2, content: "Bella rolls her eyes.  \"I doubt,\" she tells Mike when she has swallowed her bite of cake, \"that he knew I'm friends with you, but now all that troubling ignorance is resolved.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-16 02:58:00", reply_order: 7 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yep,\" Alice concurs, brightly.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-09-16 03:04:00", reply_order: 8 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 2, content: "\"Did something in particular happen last night?\" Jessica asks.<br><br>Bella doesn't really want to let Alice answer that one.  \"I was bored,\" she says.  \"And you were still sick and Angela was babysitting so I couldn't really try either of you for plans.  We went and hung out at his house.  He violated the spirit of Mozart and we invented a fictitious sport.\"<br><br>\"You could've asked me if I wanted to do something,\" Mike mutters.<br><br>\"Perhaps I would have thought of that eventually,\" says Bella.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 43, created_at: "2012-09-16 03:08:00", reply_order: 9 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 3, content: "Bella is a wise, wise person.<br><br>Alice, on the other hand, is demonstrably fond of pissing people off.<br><br>\"Whassamatter?\" he inquires of Mike, cocking his head with slightly over-exaggerated innocence.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-16 03:11:00", reply_order: 10 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 2, content: "\"I was free that afternoon, that's all,\" says Mike, giving Alice a sort of side-eye.<br><br>Bella's cake is gone.  She drops her forehead onto the heel of her hand and looks exasperatedly at Mike, but doesn't make any effort to add to this line of conversation.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 105, created_at: "2012-09-16 03:15:00", reply_order: 11 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 3, content: "Alice still isn't finished the main portion of his lunch. Without breaking eye contact with Mike, he nudges the container bearing the second slice of cake in Bella's direction.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-09-16 03:19:00", reply_order: 12 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 2, content: "Hm.  Cake or peace?  Peace or cake?<br><br>Cake.<br><br>Bella takes it.<br><br>\"Thank you,\" she says.<br><br>Mike is now actively glowering at Alice.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-16 03:20:00", reply_order: 13 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 3, content: "\"Y'welcome,\" he says cheerfully. \"Looked like you could use it.\"<br><br>And back to his inferior cafeteria food!", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-16 03:22:00", reply_order: 14 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 2, content: "\"Mike, are you okay?\" Jessica says.<br><br>\"I'm fine,\" Mike mutters.<br><br>\"Maybe you're getting Jessica's cold,\" Angela suggests.<br><br>Bella enjoys her cake.  Mmm, cake.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-16 03:23:00", reply_order: 15 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 3, content: "The cake is immensely delicious!<br><br>Alice doesn't miss it, though. There's more where that came from. And taunting Mike and pleasing Bella are both more than worth it.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-09-16 03:27:00", reply_order: 16 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 2, content: "\"So,\" Jessica says.  \"What I was going to say before I got distracted -\" this sentence is accompanied by a significant look at Alice - \"is that we should all go hang out on the beach at La Push sometime, when it gets warm, and Bella, your car is the only one that could hold a good-size group.\"<br><br>\"I'm amenable,\" says Bella.<br><br>Jessica looks at Mike, and at Alice, and says, \"Delaney can come too.  If you want to, Delaney.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-16 03:36:00", reply_order: 17 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 3, content: "He grins.<br><br>\"Sure, that'd be fun.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-09-16 03:38:00", reply_order: 18 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 2, content: "Mike gets up to toss his lunch debris.  He may actually be stomping.<br><br>Bella returns an empty Tupperware to Alice.<br><br>\"Great,\" says Jessica.  \"So that's us five, plus Lauren, and Eric - is your car the kind with extra seats in the very back?\"<br><br>\"Yeah,\" Bella says.<br><br>\"Then we can all squeeze in,\" Jessica says.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-16 03:40:00", reply_order: 19 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 3, content: "Alice leans over to watch Mike's progress towards the garbage can, then straightens to accept his Tupperware back.<br><br>He is really not trying to be subtle about the taunting, is he.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-16 03:46:00", reply_order: 20 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 2, content: "Bella gives Alice a look - it says <em>Really?</em> - and then says, \"I've been to La Push a couple times, my dad has friends there, but not recently.  Will it get at all warm anytime soon or are all these plans terribly premature?\"<br><br>\"Sometimes there's a weekend nice enough that a raincoat will do,\" Angela says, \"even in January.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-16 03:48:00", reply_order: 21 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 3, content: "Alice answers her look with an unconcerned shrug.<br><br>\"I don't even know where that is,\" he contributes.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-16 03:54:00", reply_order: 22 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 2, content: "\"It's the Indian reservation about half an hour's drive away,\" Jessica says.  \"There are Indians there.\"<br><br>\"Quileutes,\" Angela says, possibly in lieu of correcting Jessica on her ethnic terminology.<br><br>\"There's nice scenery,\" Bella says.  \"The residents don't mind people hanging out there, generally.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-16 03:56:00", reply_order: 23 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 3, content: "\"Cool,\" he says, shrugging again and opening his bottle of juice. \"I mean, not that scenery is my favourite thing in the whole wide world, but it's okay.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-16 04:01:00", reply_order: 24 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 2, content: "Mike has taken a long route back to the table.  He has also harvested Lauren and Eric from wherever they were sitting, and now it's a little crowded.<br><br>\"Whoa,\" Eric says to Mike, upon spotting Alice.  \"You weren't kidding.\"<br><br>\"It'd be a dumb joke,\" Lauren says, \"just to say that someone was sitting here if he wasn't.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-16 04:03:00", reply_order: 25 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 3, content: "\"Hi,\" says Alice, waving at the newcomers. \"You've sure got a lot of friends,\" he adds, turning to Bella. \"I didn't accidentally drop in on the popular crowd, did I? Because that would be tragically hilarious.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-09-16 04:06:00", reply_order: 26 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 2, content: "\"Yeah, tragic and hilarious, both at once,\" Lauren says.<br><br>\"I don't really have a good sense of those dynamics here yet,\" Bella says.<br><br>\"It's not like we're cheerleaders and football,\" Jessica says.  \"Well, I'm going to try out for cheer next year, but you know what I mean.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-16 04:08:00", reply_order: 27 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 3, content: "\"I'm pretty sure there's not a football player left at this school who can look me in the eye without trying to punch it,\" Alice muses.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-16 04:09:00", reply_order: 28 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 2, content: "\"Is that because you're obnoxious?\" Mike asks, in what is for him a bold move.<br><br>\"Mike,\" says Bella testily.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 105, created_at: "2012-09-16 04:10:00", reply_order: 29 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yep,\" he says brightly. \"Glad you noticed.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-09-16 04:12:00", reply_order: 30 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 2, content: "\"Bella, why are you hanging out with this jerk?\" Mike asks pleadingly.<br><br>\"Apparently,\" Bella says in a dark, level tone, \"I have poor taste in companions.\"<br><br>That one takes Mike a second.  He spends that second in rather adorable triumph, which evaporates.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 105, created_at: "2012-09-16 04:14:00", reply_order: 31 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 3, content: "Ooh, <em>good</em> one. Alice grins behind his juice.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-09-16 04:16:00", reply_order: 32 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 2, content: "Mike's done with his lunch anyway.  He just leaves.<br><br>\"Well, that was kind of a bitchy thing to do,\" Lauren remarks.<br><br>\"So was that,\" says Bella without any particular heat.  Or interest.<br><br>Angela's trying to hide her face in her shoulder.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 105, created_at: "2012-09-16 04:17:00", reply_order: 33 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 3, content: "Alice glances sideways at Bella and grins again.<br><br>He doesn't <em>say</em> 'I love you', but he thinks it pretty loudly.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-16 04:20:00", reply_order: 34 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 2, content: "He gets a wan smile for his trouble.<br><br>Bella then conspicuously asks if Angela wants to start heading for Bio, because she actually likes Angela.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 43, created_at: "2012-09-16 04:21:00", reply_order: 35 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 3, content: "Alice, not being finished his juice yet, stays right where he is.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-16 04:23:00", reply_order: 36 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 2, content: "Lauren waits until Bella's gone and then turns to Alice.  \"So, did you move here because you, like, killed somebody?\"<br><br>Jessica was about to leave, but apparently can't pass up the chance to hear the answer.  Eric's leaving anyway.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-16 04:27:00", reply_order: 37 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 3, content: "<br><br><br><br>He grins.<br><br>\"I could tell you that,\" he says with a wink, \"but I'd have to kill you.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-09-16 04:28:00", reply_order: 38 },
  { post_id: 7, user_id: 2, content: "Jessica, slightly quicker on the uptake than Lauren, comes to the understanding that this sentence has implications.  She departs expeditiously.<br><br>Lauren cocks her head, then leaves, apparently mostly because she and Alice are the only people left at the table.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-16 04:32:00", reply_order: 39 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 3, content: "The first words Delaney Hammond, Sr. says to his prospective attorney are, \"What in God's name took you so long?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-28 22:27:00", reply_order: 0 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 2, content: "\"Car trouble,\" Paul says shortly.  \"My sincerest apologies.  And,\" <em>wince</em>, \"the lost time isn't billable.\"  Stupid law firm caring about its stupid reputation for stupid good-faith operations because it defends stupid criminals.  Paul's developing a stomachache.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-28 22:29:00", reply_order: 1 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 3, content: "\"You don't have to look so constipated about it,\" says Mr. Hammond. \"You'll have enough of a chance to wring me dry while you're actually working for me.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-28 22:32:00", reply_order: 2 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 2, content: "\"Ah.  Ah, yes, our firm's associates in New York with whom you've previously contracted recommended me to you, I believe?  I believe the trial's already been scheduled, so it might behoove you to select your lawyer quickly, and I am already here.  Reportedly the prosecution already has all of the evidence it wants.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-28 22:35:00", reply_order: 3 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yeah,\" he says, grumblingly, and names an hourly rate that is indeed <em>very nice</em>. \"How's that sound?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-28 22:38:00", reply_order: 4 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 2, content: "\"Perfect, Mr. Hammond.  Now, employed as your attorney, everything you say to me falls under attorney-client privilege; I will defend you regardless of the situation at hand; and these trials are often decided on charisma and technicalities regardless, so it is never in your best interest to lie to me.  That having been established, what <em>did</em> happen regarding the topic under discussion?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-28 22:40:00", reply_order: 5 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 3, content: "\"What do you think?\" he growls.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-28 22:42:00", reply_order: 6 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 2, content: "\"I know that the prosecution is making such extensive and specific allegations that their evidence packet couldn't be sent as a single e-mail attachment,\" Paul says.  \"That's very irregular for a child abuse charge.  My computer broke this morning and so I won't be able to look over what the prosecution has to say until I get it repaired or replaced, but we don't want our jury to get their facts from the prosecution <em>anyway</em>.  What's your version?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-28 22:45:00", reply_order: 7 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 3, content: "\"My version is, if that little demon could stay out of trouble for five straight minutes, maybe I could be a little gentler with him,\" says Mr. Hammond. \"But I don't think you want to say that to a jury, or not in so many words.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-28 23:11:00", reply_order: 8 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 2, content: "\"Not in so many words,\" Paul says, \"no.  But we may be able to sway them by painting your son as an incorrigible troublemaking delinquent, while also downplaying the severity of the disciplinary action.  What do we have to work with for the troublemaking delinquency?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-28 23:18:00", reply_order: 9 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 3, content: "\"He starts fights at school like clockwork,\" is the first thing to come to mind. \"Never goes to class, hasn't done any homework in years, his room is a sty, he can't keep his foul mouth shut at the dinner table...\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-28 23:27:00", reply_order: 10 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 2, content: "Paul privately decides he's going to need to do most of his work at jury selection time.  \"Anything he'd have a record for?  Truancy, assault?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-28 23:29:00", reply_order: 11 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 3, content: "\"He <em>nearly</em> got arrested for prostitution in New York,\" Mr. Hammond admits grudgingly. \"Didn't quite, though. I've spent a lot of effort over the years keeping him <em>out</em> of the hands of police, and this is how he repays me.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-28 23:35:00", reply_order: 12 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 2, content: "Not a flicker of surprise at that word crosses Paul's face.  \"Okay.  That all?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-28 23:38:00", reply_order: 13 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 3, content: "\"All the highlights, anyway,\" he says.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-28 23:40:00", reply_order: 14 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 2, content: "\"Details could be very important,\" coaxes Paul.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-28 23:51:00", reply_order: 15 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 3, content: "\"He steals his mother's clothing and makeup,\" says Mr. Hammond.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-28 23:52:00", reply_order: 16 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 2, content: "\"Speaking of which.  How is your wife liable to handle this?  She can't be compelled to testify against you, but could be useful in our favor.\"<br><br>Paul's obviously assuming that she's on their side.  Oh, Paul.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-28 23:54:00", reply_order: 17 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 3, content: "\"My <em>wife</em>,\" he growls, \"abandoned ship. I don't know that she'll have the stones to say a word against me, but she won't say one for me, that's for damn sure.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-28 23:58:00", reply_order: 18 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 2, content: "\"Ah.\"  Pause.  \"What does she know?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 00:00:00", reply_order: 19 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 3, content: "\"Most of it,\" says Mr. Hammond. \"Including what an incorrigible monster she gave birth to, but apparently that doesn't sway her any.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-29 00:02:00", reply_order: 20 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 2, content: "\"None of that language at the trial,\" Paul remarks.  \"Okay.  We'll hope she declines to testify.  The prosecutor has your son, presumably - who else can they call that we need to prepare for?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 00:04:00", reply_order: 21 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 3, content: "\"My driver's probably seen a few things, but I don't know that they'll manage to squeeze any out of him.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-29 00:08:00", reply_order: 22 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 2, content: "\"Even if they sit him down and put him under oath?\" Paul asks.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 00:25:00", reply_order: 23 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 3, content: "\"If they have to get him to admit he knows something first, I doubt they'll get that far. But who knows. If Judith can grow a spine at this late hour, maybe he can too.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-29 00:27:00", reply_order: 24 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 2, content: "\"Mm.  Well.  Let's be honest, if your wife testifies - and possibly even if she doesn't - your odds are not good.  How do you feel about plea bargaining?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 00:29:00", reply_order: 25 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 3, content: "He makes an eloquently disgusted face.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-29 00:30:00", reply_order: 26 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 2, content: "\"You realize that if you have me turn down a plea bargain for you, and we lose, you're looking at five years - minimum - and that doesn't even begin to cover the reputational and other consequences.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 00:33:00", reply_order: 27 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 3, content: "\"The reputational consequences have been and gone,\" he says. \"What's a plea bargain going to get me?", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-29 00:37:00", reply_order: 28 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 2, content: "\"Sentence reduction.  Possibly immediate parole, with or without damages awarded, with something like a restraining order preventing you from seeing your son, but no other restrictions.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 00:39:00", reply_order: 29 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 3, content: "Mr. Hammond harrumphs.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-29 00:40:00", reply_order: 30 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 2, content: "\"It would be better than jail.  It's possible that I can get you acquitted altogether, but it's by no means guaranteed, Mr. Hammond.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 00:40:00", reply_order: 31 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 3, content: "\"I'll think about it,\" he allows.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-29 00:42:00", reply_order: 32 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 2, content: "\"I'll call you later today, then, before the meeting where that would have to be handled.  Is there anything else I should know before I find a computer store?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 00:43:00", reply_order: 33 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 3, content: "\"Don't think so,\" says Mr. Hammond.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-29 00:44:00", reply_order: 34 },
  { post_id: 15, user_id: 2, content: "\"Have a good day, then, Mr. Hammond,\" Paul says, nodding and getting up to leave.<br><br>He isn't even surprised when he bumps into someone two steps out the door and falls over, nor when this results in him also needing to find a drycleaner as soon as possible.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 00:46:00", reply_order: 35 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "Alice answers it.<br><br>\"Hi!\" he says. [Bella, do you know this lady?]", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:01:00", reply_order: 0 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "[No, but she's wearing lawyer clothes.  I think the standard way to find out who she is is \"can I help you?\"]<br><br>\"Hello!\" says Lucinda.  \"Is this the Swan residence?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:02:00", reply_order: 1 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yep,\" says Alice. \"Why, did you want a Swan?\"<br><br>It's... kind of close! A little!<br><br>He's not very good at standards.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:04:00", reply_order: 2 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"Actually, I'm looking for Delaney Hammond, Jr.,\" says Lucinda.  \"And Chief Swan said I could look here.\"<br><br>[Ask her flat out if she's Delaney Hammond Jr.'s lawyer, before you even identify yourself,] Bella advises.  [Even if Charlie sent her, and she could be lying.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:05:00", reply_order: 3 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "[I love you,] he says. Because she is full of useful advice, even when he doesn't follow it.<br><br>\"And what do you want Delaney Hammond, Jr. for?\" he inquires. (And even manages not to suggest any options. She doesn't look like she'd bite, anyway.)", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:07:00", reply_order: 4 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"I'm his lawyer,\" Lucinda.  \"My name is Lucinda Daly.  Assistant State's Attorney.  Is he here?\"<br><br>[Okay, swell.  Let 'er in.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:09:00", reply_order: 5 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"You're lookin' at him,\" he says, and steps back out of the doorway. \"C'mon in.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:10:00", reply_order: 6 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"Thank you.  Chief Swan referred to you as Laney; is that what you prefer to be called?\" asks Lucinda.  \"And are you comfortable talking here?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:11:00", reply_order: 7 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yeah, sure,\" he says to both of those things.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:15:00", reply_order: 8 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"All right.  Now, I've read over my copy of the notebook that was submitted as evidence, and the medical reports that the police retrieved, but is there anything else I should know?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:16:00", reply_order: 9 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "Alice considers. Or, well, consults.<br><br>[<em>Now</em> do I talk about why we moved?]", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:17:00", reply_order: 10 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "[It's not in your interest to lie to her.  She doesn't have any reason to report anything you've done to anyone who'd get you in trouble for it.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:18:00", reply_order: 11 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"Well,\" he says. \"The reason we moved here is 'cause I got raped in New York and Dad decided I'd been hooking. So he might try to throw that at me and see if it sticks.\"<br><br>It's not actually a lie as such. But he wants to see how she reacts, and whether she wants to hear the rest, before he tells it.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:27:00", reply_order: 12 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "Lucinda does blink, but only just.  \"Is the incident in any kind of official record?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:29:00", reply_order: 13 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"Fucked if I know, but I doubt it. Official records and my dad don't get along.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:30:00", reply_order: 14 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"Okay.  I can probably get out about half a sentence about that before the defense lawyer objects, then, and it's anyone's guess if the judge will let me carry on from there.\"  She produces some notes and consults them briefly.  \"The notebooks of documentation were submitted with a note saying that you have an eidetic memory, which is how you were able to remember all those events for your friend to write down; is that right?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:32:00", reply_order: 15 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yep,\" he says.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:34:00", reply_order: 16 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"We might want to prove that in court.  Some simple feat of memory that almost no one could do.  That will go a long way to indicating that the documentation wasn't pure fabrication.  I'm sure we can think of something, but if you have a stock party trick to show it off, that's liable to work too.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:35:00", reply_order: 17 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"I don't usually show it off,\" he says.<br><br>[Any ideas?]", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:36:00", reply_order: 18 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "[Ask everyone in the jury to write down some random numbers and letters, you get exactly a second to look at each paper, the jury get their papers back, you read off the strings,] Bella says.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:37:00", reply_order: 19 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "...he loves her. So much.<br><br>Alice repeats this suggestion almost word for word, pausing periodically as though he is thinking it up on the spot.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:39:00", reply_order: 20 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"That'll do,\" Lucinda says.  \"The notebooks also included several mentions of injuries serious enough to leave marks.  This is the sort of thing we want to be able to provide more evidence of, but we don't want you getting half-naked in the courtroom either; photographs in advance are the best choice.  I can take them, or if you have someone you're more comfortable with available, that will work too.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:42:00", reply_order: 21 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"Don't really care,\" he says, shrugging easily. \"Might as well be you.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:44:00", reply_order: 22 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "Lucinda nods and produces a camera.  There is a pretty much silent photo shoot.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:44:00", reply_order: 23 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "Alice indicates the provenance of various marks—this one from the time his dad broke his ribs in November, that one from a ruler, those ones from a cane. A nasty-looking knife scar across his left hip gets \"not Dad, don't bother\". As previously indicated, he exhibits no strong feelings about the process.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:49:00", reply_order: 24 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "Lucinda makes notes about which photos correspond to which incidents, and, when she's got them all, puts the camera away.  \"Now,\" she says.  \"This case is pretty much going to convict or acquit based on your testimony.  Do you feel able to do that - sympathetically, convincingly, for as long as it takes?  If not, I can see if the defense is up for a plea bargain, but I think we can win this outright if you testify well.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:51:00", reply_order: 25 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"I dunno how sympathetic I am, but I'll give it my best shot,\" he says. \"And I'm not gonna quit in the middle, that's for fucking sure.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:56:00", reply_order: 26 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"Well,\" Lucinda says.  \"Sympatheticness tips: hold the cursing.  Possibly excepting if you're about to burst into tears - which you <em>can</em> do, but ideally not more than once or twice.\"<br><br>[Tell her about getting into fights at school <em>and why</em>,] Bella recommends.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 01:58:00", reply_order: 27 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"Okay,\" says Alice. \"Oh, uh—I got into a lot of fights at school so nobody'd look twice if I showed up with bruises. Is that relevant?\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:00:00", reply_order: 28 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"Yes.  I'll make sure you have a chance to mention that,\" Lucinda says.  \"Especially if the defense tries to paint you in a negative light for the behavior.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:01:00", reply_order: 29 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"Pretty sure the only reason I wasn't constantly getting in shit for it was because he knew I was covering for him.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:10:00", reply_order: 30 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"The defense attorney's going to ask <em>why</em> you were covering,\" Lucinda says, \"and you want to have an answer ready.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:16:00", reply_order: 31 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"I lived in his <em>house</em>,\" he says. \"If I'd tried this back in New York I would be <em>in</em> his house, and he would not be making me tea and cupcakes.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:20:00", reply_order: 32 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"And now you have somewhere else to go?\" Lucinda asks, gesturing at the Swan residence.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:21:00", reply_order: 33 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yep,\" says Alice.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:22:00", reply_order: 34 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"All right.  If I were the defense, next I'd ask you why you didn't trust the police to protect you if you went to them in New York.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:23:00", reply_order: 35 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"'Cause the first thing I ever learned about cops is that enough money will make 'em go away,\" he says, \"and it took me this long to unlearn it.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:28:00", reply_order: 36 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"That would probably be better presented as a story about the unlearning, rather than dwelling on the original mistrust,\" Lucinda advises.  \"Am I correct in guessing that Chief Swan was personally involved there?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:30:00", reply_order: 37 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"Kinda, yeah,\" he says. [You mind if your name comes up?]", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:32:00", reply_order: 38 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "[Go ahead.]<br><br>\"Kind of?\" Lucinda asks.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:32:00", reply_order: 39 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"I made friends with his daughter,\" he says. \"And, you know, she believes in her dad. Which was weird on a number of levels. She brought me around pretty quick, though.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:34:00", reply_order: 40 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "Lucinda obviously thinks this is adorable.  \"That's lovely.  We might want to call her up to testify too, to corroborate what you have to say.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:35:00", reply_order: 41 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"I can ask her,\" he says. [Or I could offer to go get you.]", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:39:00", reply_order: 42 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"Is she home?\"<br><br>[You can come get me, yeah.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:40:00", reply_order: 43 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yup,\" he says. \"Just a sec.\"<br><br>And off he goes in search of Bella, not that he expects it to be much of a search.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:41:00", reply_order: 44 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "Bella meets him in the upstairs hallway, and clunks down on her crutches for the sound effect.<br><br>\"Hello, Miss Swan,\" says Lucinda.<br><br>\"Please call me Bella,\" says Bella.<br><br>\"All right.  You're comfortable testifying?\"<br><br>Bella nods.  \"I'll have to anyway, won't I?  The notebooks are in my handwriting.\"<br><br>\"Well, it would be something of a problem if you didn't want to,\" Lucinda says.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:43:00", reply_order: 45 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "[Should I try to not obviously have a crush on you in front of the lawyer?] he thinks to ask.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:44:00", reply_order: 46 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "[I don't see how it'd matter,] Bella says.  [Why?]<br><br>\"Well, I don't mind.  I've been missing school anyway, since I was hit by a car,\" Bella says, gesturing at the \"broken arm\".<br><br>\"I hadn't been planning to ask, but I'm glad you're recovering, at any rate,\" says Lucinda.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:46:00", reply_order: 47 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "[Dunno,] he says, with a very slight shrug. [Thought I'd ask just in case.] Since it is permissible, though, he lets himself smile at her.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:51:00", reply_order: 48 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"All right,\" Lucinda says.  \"Unless either of you can think of anything, I'm going to go find Mrs. Hammond and speak to her.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:54:00", reply_order: 49 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "Naturally, Alice glances at Bella, who between the two of them is definitely the thinker of things.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:55:00", reply_order: 50 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"Mr. Hammond is reasonably likely to try to buy his way out of this,\" Bella says.  \"If there's anything extra you can do to watch out for jury tampering, please do it.  My dad's pretty sure of the judge, though.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 43, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:57:00", reply_order: 51 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "Yeah. Things like that.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 02:57:00", reply_order: 52 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"I'll keep an eye out,\" Lucinda says.<br><br>\"That's all I can think of right now, but perhaps we could get your phone number,\" Bella continues.<br><br>Lucinda nods and writes it down for them.  \"I'll see you in a few days, if not before,\" she says, and she gets up to go.  \"Bye, Laney, Bella.\"<br><br>\"Bye,\" says Bella.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 03:01:00", reply_order: 53 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"Bye,\" Alice echoes. \"Thanks.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-09-29 03:05:00", reply_order: 54 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"So,\" Bella says, when Lucinda has gone.  \"She seems decent.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 03:06:00", reply_order: 55 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yep,\" says Alice. \"Man, how bad am I gonna fuck up the sympathetic thing?\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 03:07:00", reply_order: 56 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"Depends on how hard you try not to.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 03:08:00", reply_order: 57 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"I will try really fucking hard!\" he says. \"But I don't know how the fuck normal people work.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 03:08:00", reply_order: 58 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"Well, I'll be there, I can coach you in realtime,\" Bella soothes, patting his head.  \"Just take a second before speaking aloud - and look thoughtful or emotional while you do it - to let me see what you're going to say and make corrections.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 43, created_at: "2012-09-29 03:10:00", reply_order: 59 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "He leans into her hand.<br><br>\"I love you,\" he sighs. That is definitely the most prominent of the many emotions he is currently experiencing.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 03:12:00", reply_order: 60 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "Bella smiles.  Pat pat pat.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 03:13:00", reply_order: 61 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"Purr purr,\" he says, grinning.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-09-29 03:26:00", reply_order: 62 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "Bella laughs.<br><br>\"I think this is going to turn out fine,\" she says.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 03:27:00", reply_order: 63 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"Well, then I guess I believe you.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-29 03:28:00", reply_order: 64 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "Meanwhile, Lucinda arrives at the place where Judith has been placed.  Apparently they're just putting her up in a motel.  \"Mrs. Hammond?\" she calls, knocking.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 03:43:00", reply_order: 65 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "Judith answers the door—begowned as usual, but with her makeup slightly less than perfect.<br><br>\"Yes?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-29 03:44:00", reply_order: 66 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"Hello, Mrs. Hammond.  I'm Lucinda Daly, and I'm prosecuting your husband's case.  Do you have a few minutes to talk?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 03:51:00", reply_order: 67 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"Certainly,\" she says. \"Do you want to come in? I'm afraid I don't have much to offer as a hostess at the moment.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-29 03:52:00", reply_order: 68 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"I understand,\" Lucinda says, stepping in.  She sits in one of the rickety little chairs in the room.  \"Do you intend to testify against your husband?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 03:53:00", reply_order: 69 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"If it would help—and I imagine it would—yes.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-29 03:54:00", reply_order: 70 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"It would, yes.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 03:55:00", reply_order: 71 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"Then I will.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-29 03:56:00", reply_order: 72 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"If I were the defense,\" Lucinda says, \"I would make sure to ask you why you never came forward.  Do you have an answer for that?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 03:57:00", reply_order: 73 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"It didn't happen all at once,\" she says. \"He started out so <em>reasonable</em>... and by the time it was clear that he wasn't reasonable at all, well, I wasn't sure just how unreasonable he could get. And I didn't want to find out.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-29 04:01:00", reply_order: 74 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"So you thought that if you did anything, he might turn on you,\" Lucinda says.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 04:01:00", reply_order: 75 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yes.\"<br><br>Well, it was among her reasons, anyway.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-29 04:02:00", reply_order: 76 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"All right, that will do.  Is there anything else you think I should know?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 04:03:00", reply_order: 77 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"...He has a temper,\" she says. \"You might consider getting him to lose it.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-29 04:06:00", reply_order: 78 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"Any suggestions?\" inquires Lucinda.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 04:06:00", reply_order: 79 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "She rubs her left hand with her right.<br><br>\"Well, he was awfully upset when I told him I'm leaving him,\" she murmurs.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-29 04:09:00", reply_order: 80 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "Lucinda nods, and waits, in case there's more.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 04:09:00", reply_order: 81 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"And Junior, of course. A week doesn't go by where he isn't angry with Junior. But I don't know that that will help you any.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-29 04:12:00", reply_order: 82 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"That's already the subject of the trial, yes.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 04:12:00", reply_order: 83 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"He doesn't like to feel disrespected or slandered,\" she says. \"Even about fairly inconsequential things. He is never happy to be disagreed with.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-29 04:17:00", reply_order: 84 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "Lucinda nods.<br><br>\"Thank you.  Is there anything else I ought to hear before I go?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 04:17:00", reply_order: 85 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 3, content: "\"No,\" she says, after considering for a moment. \"I don't think so.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-29 04:18:00", reply_order: 86 },
  { post_id: 16, user_id: 2, content: "\"Thank you for your time,\" says Lucinda, and she goes.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-29 04:19:00", reply_order: 87 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 3, content: "[Ooh, a crowd,] says Alice from across the lunchroom. [Want me to distract 'em?]", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-09-30 21:58:00", reply_order: 0 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 2, content: "[Be gentle.  And don't interfere with Jessica; she's being helpful, she wants to tell everyone everything herself.]", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-30 21:59:00", reply_order: 1 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 3, content: "[Can do,] he says cheerfully, and makes his way to her table. This time there is no conveniently empty seat, so he steals a chair from the next table over, drags it up to the end of hers, and gently nudges her tray down a few inches to make room for his.<br><br>\"Hi, Bella,\" he says. \"Hi, crowd. Cupcake?\"<br><br>And indeed, he opens up today's Tupperware container to reveal two tiers of whimsical cupcakes. That is not what it originally contained, but no one is going to know the difference. ", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-09-30 22:06:00", reply_order: 2 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 2, content: "\"Ooh,\" says Bella, taking a cupcake.  The rest of the cupcakes also disappear in short order, and the members of the crowd have their mouths full.  [You're going to risk being popular or something if you do this regularly,] Bella points out.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-30 22:10:00", reply_order: 3 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 3, content: "[Watch me care,] he says, munching on a cupcake that has a stormcloud mosaic picked out on the top in various shades of blue and grey jelly beans.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-30 22:11:00", reply_order: 4 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 2, content: "Bella smiles to herself.  She finishes her cupcake and goes through the rest of her lunch quickly, before the onslaught begins again.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-30 22:14:00", reply_order: 5 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 3, content: "Success! Alice starts in on his own lunch, which apart from the cupcakes is really quite boring.<br><br>...Come to think of it, he's done something publicly interesting recently too, hasn't he?", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-09-30 22:15:00", reply_order: 6 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 2, content: "[I haven't told anyone, so unless you have, it might just not have filtered down yet,] Bella says.  [It's not like Theo or Hilary have kids in high school.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-30 22:16:00", reply_order: 7 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 3, content: "[Guess not. Huh. Well, I'll be enjoying that while it lasts.] He so does not envy Bella her position at the centre of everyone's attention.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-30 22:18:00", reply_order: 8 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 2, content: "[It'll die down in a few days.]<br><br>She's done eating.  She decides to leave very early for Bio, where only Angela will be able to follow.<br><br>Classes are both duller (because she pentagoned all of them, because she wants both good grades and spare time) and more interesting (because her brain is now her notebook, and she can space out and think about whatever she likes), now.<br><br>Bio starts, Bio ends, gym class time.  Bella wonders if anyone has noticed that she isn't tripping, yet.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-30 22:20:00", reply_order: 9 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 3, content: "Predictably, Alice is talking to Ms. Finch. He waves at Bella when she enters the gym.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-30 22:22:00", reply_order: 10 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 2, content: "Bella trots up to them.  \"Hi, Ms. Finch,\" she says.  \"I have a weird request.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-30 22:23:00", reply_order: 11 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 3, content: "\"Hi, Bella! I have a reasonable answer,\" says Ms. Finch. Alice laughs.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-09-30 22:24:00", reply_order: 12 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 2, content: "\"Well,\" Bella says.  \"I still don't have an actual <em>diagnosis</em> - but what I think happened is that I had something knocked loose in one of my ears, and that caused my balance issues.  And now they're just... Even on <em>crutches</em> I wasn't falling over.  I haven't had a near miss on tumbling down the stairs or slipped walking on ice since the accident.  I think getting hit by a car managed to knock my ear how it's supposed to be.  And I want to fold into regular gym class.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 43, created_at: "2012-09-30 22:26:00", reply_order: 13 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 3, content: "\"You ar a very lucky person,\" says Ms. Finch. \"And, luckily, we're starting something new tomorrow. Do what you want today, and tomorrow you can approach badminton with a hopefully ordinary amount of ignorance.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-30 22:33:00", reply_order: 14 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 2, content: "Bella nods, smiling.  \"Don't need me to do a cartwheel or three to check?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-30 22:33:00", reply_order: 15 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 3, content: "\"Nope,\" she says. \"Something tells me you're unusually motivated right now not to do anything that'll get you hurt. Besides, if you successfully did a cartwheel I'd have to find out who taught them to you while you were still Little Miss Klutz, and then I'd have to decide whether to shake their hand or drop them in the scorpion pit.\"<br><br>...Alice giggles.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-09-30 22:40:00", reply_order: 16 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 2, content: "Bella laughs.  \"It was just an example.  Scorpion pit, honestly.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-30 23:25:00", reply_order: 17 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 3, content: "\"Scorpion pit,\" Ms. Finch confirms, with perhaps more cheer than is strictly necessary. \"You can quit snickering any day now, Hammond.\"<br><br>\"Nope,\" says Alice, and Ms. Finch cracks a smile.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-09-30 23:27:00", reply_order: 18 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 2, content: "\"I didn't think a school this size would have the budget for a scorpion pit,\" Bella muses.<br><br>[You liable to tell Ms. Finch about your dad?]  Bella reads him, too, because why not.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-30 23:29:00", reply_order: 19 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 3, content: "\"When did I say it belonged to the school?\" inquires Ms. Finch.<br><br>[Maybe,] says Alice. [If it comes up.] He has, if possible, mixed apathy about the idea. On the one hand, he doesn't really care to keep it from her, and on the other hand, he doesn't really care to let her know.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-30 23:31:00", reply_order: 20 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 2, content: "\"Ah, your <em>personal</em> scorpion pit.  Makes much more sense.\"<br><br>[What would be the downside to telling her?]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-30 23:32:00", reply_order: 21 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 3, content: "\"Doesn't it?\" agrees Ms. Finch.<br><br>\"If somebody around here was gonna have a scorpion pit, it would definitely be you,\" says Alice.<br><br>[Downside to her knowing? Not really any. Downside to <em>telling</em> her? I have to, like, talk about it. She might decide to hug me.] He glances at her as though to assess the risk of hugs. [Okay, probably not,] he concedes, [but it could happen.]", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-09-30 23:36:00", reply_order: 22 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 2, content: "[You want me to tell her?] Bella proposes.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-30 23:36:00", reply_order: 23 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 3, content: "[Sure!]<br><br>Bella has such great solutions to things.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-30 23:37:00", reply_order: 24 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 2, content: "[With you here or off someplace?]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-30 23:38:00", reply_order: 25 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 3, content: "[Second one? And probably not right now anyway, because class is starting.] Indeed, Ms. Finch is turning to greet the influx of students.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-30 23:40:00", reply_order: 26 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 2, content: "[Right.  After.]  Bella fetches her mat.  She'll sit through one more day of stretching and bodyweight exercises and yoga, out of everyone's way, and then she gets to play.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-30 23:40:00", reply_order: 27 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 3, content: "Alice sticks around for class, but departs afterward without stopping for a chat. Hilary is coming to pick him up and take him grocery shopping, and he expects her to be prompt.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-30 23:48:00", reply_order: 28 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 2, content: "[Seeya.]<br><br>Bella hangs back.  She waits till the place is clear of non-Ms.-Finches.  When this is the case, she says, \"Ms. Finch?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-30 23:49:00", reply_order: 29 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 3, content: "[Toodles,] he says cheerfully, just as he spots Hilary's car turning into the lot.<br><br>\"Hi,\" says Ms. Finch. \"Again.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-09-30 23:53:00", reply_order: 30 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 2, content: "\"Laney\" (Ms. Finch would probably understand 'Alice', but that would be a distraction right now) \"doesn't want to talk about it himself, but he said I could tell you - the other day his father was sentenced to fifteen years in prison.  For child abuse.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 43, created_at: "2012-09-30 23:54:00", reply_order: 31 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 3, content: "Ms. Finch blinks.<br><br>And rubs her hands over her face.<br><br>\"Wish I could say I'm surprised,\" she remarks. \"What kind?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-30 23:57:00", reply_order: 32 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 2, content: "\"The beating him up every day or three kind,\" Bella says.  \"I mean, there was verbal mixed in too, but that wasn't the bulk of the charges.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-30 23:58:00", reply_order: 33 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yeah,\" says Ms. Finch. \"Again: wish I could say I'm surprised, but I'm not. It's been pretty obvious since he got here that there is some part of that kid's life that is immensely fucked up.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-30 23:59:00", reply_order: 34 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 2, content: "\"I think most of that is actually just him being himself, but yeah,\" Bella says.  \"I think he'll get into fewer fights now.  Possibly no fights at all.  He won't be acquiring other injuries to cover for.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 00:04:00", reply_order: 35 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yes,\" Ms. Finch agrees. \"He's being himself, and himself is immensely fucked up.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-01 02:00:00", reply_order: 36 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 2, content: "Bella nods, shrugs.  \"Well, I guess I'll call my dad and get my ride home now,\" she says, stepping away with a wave.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 02:01:00", reply_order: 37 },
  { post_id: 18, user_id: 3, content: "\"See ya,\" says Ms. Finch.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-01 04:17:00", reply_order: 38 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "[Want me to drop in with cupcakes again?] queries Alice from the lunch line.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 04:52:00", reply_order: 0 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "[Cupcakes in particular should most likely be a one time thing,] Bella says.  [If you have another equally clever idea I'd like to see it - otherwise I'll just sit through this until I'm done eating, I think.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 43, created_at: "2012-10-01 04:53:00", reply_order: 1 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "Okay. So, benign interventions that distract attention from her. Doesn't necessarily have to give everyone tasty things, although maybe he could wish up some cookies.<br><br>Yeah, that seems like an adequate plan. Absent objections from Bella, he is going to descend on her table with his Tupperware of Mystery (he brought an empty one today, just to cover for tricks like this) and fill it with assorted cookies on the way.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 05:18:00", reply_order: 2 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "[That's very like cupcakes, you realize.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 05:19:00", reply_order: 3 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "[Yup. And that wasn't a no.]<br><br>He's halfway across the room, but he hasn't materialized the cookies yet.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-10-01 05:20:00", reply_order: 4 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "[Meh.]<br><br>Pause.<br><br>[Lemon cookies,] she suggests.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 05:20:00", reply_order: 5 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "[Sure.]<br><br>There are indeed lemon cookies in the mix, when he finally sits down, opens the container, and wordlessly sets it in the middle of the table. But because Alice is a fundamentally assorted person, lemon only makes up about 30% of the stock.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 05:24:00", reply_order: 6 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "Bella snags herself a lemon cookie.  And one of those tempting raspberry things, too.<br><br>But the ploy isn't as effective now that the conversation is about Alice.<br><br>\"You sent your own dad to jail?\" challenges Mike.<br><br>\"What're you gonna do with three million dollars?\" asks Lauren.<br><br>\"Are you seeing a shrink?  You should.  My aunt's a shrink,\" Jessica says.<br><br>\"Why did you wait until <em>now</em> to make a fuss about it?\" Eric wants to know.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-01 05:27:00", reply_order: 7 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "He raises his eyebrows, looks around the table, shrugs, picks up a plain old chocolate chip, and takes a big bite.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 05:28:00", reply_order: 8 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "\"Hello?\" snaps Mike.<br><br>Jessica just repeats her question louder.  Eric backs off.<br><br>\"I mean wow,\" Lauren rambles.  \"Three million dollars.  I'd get, like, a boat.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-01 05:31:00", reply_order: 9 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "Alice smiles brightly at Eric, and with some amusement at Lauren, and with some contempt at Mike, and takes his time finishing his cookie.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-01 05:33:00", reply_order: 10 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "\"De-laaaaa-neeeey,\" says Jessica, waving her hand in front of his face.  \"If you're going to come over here, be sociable.\"<br><br>\"Whatever, don't waste your time on that freak,\" Mike mutters.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 102, created_at: "2012-10-01 05:38:00", reply_order: 11 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "You know, part of him thought that being in such a generally fantastic mood lately and have his life be, on the whole, so very much better would take a little of the sting out of that word.<br><br>Nope.<br><br>He doesn't show it, though.<br><br>He ignores Jessica like she isn't even there, cocks his head at Mike, and says, \"Okay, no, I'm curious. How is the fact that I sent my dad to jail a <em>bad</em> thing?\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 05:42:00", reply_order: 12 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "[Temper,] Bella warns.<br><br>\"He's your <em>dad</em>,\" Mike says.  \"I can't believe he even put up with you, if I acted like you mine would send me to military school, and then you turned around and trumped something up for the cops.\"<br><br>Bella coughs.  Mike doesn't even look at her.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 105, created_at: "2012-10-01 05:44:00", reply_order: 13 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "He ignores Bella, too. Or he hears her, but he doesn't care. It's not like he's kicking the guy's ass or anything.<br><br>\"Is this you trying to get my shirt off? 'Cause you could've just asked,\" he says. \"I didn't trump up shit and I've got the scars to prove it. Ever broken a bone? You hear it before you feel it, didja know that? <em>Snap</em>,\" he says, smacking the edge of the table lightly for emphasis. \"<em>Then</em> it hurts.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-10-01 05:57:00", reply_order: 14 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "\"You've broken bones because you antagonize people, classmates, football players,\" Mike says.  \"I've <em>seen you do it</em>, everyone has, you must have had one hell of a slick lawyer.  Keep your clothes on, prick, I know what I know.\"<br><br>\"Mike, shut <em>up</em>,\" Bella says.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-01 05:59:00", reply_order: 15 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"Sure I do,\" he says. \"But none of those assholes ever put me in the hospital. <em>Daddy</em>, on the other hand, dragged me all the way downstairs to the fireplace just so he could beat me with the poker. So all in all I am pretty fucking glad I put him in jail.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 06:04:00", reply_order: 16 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "\"You must've deserved it,\" says Mike.  Angela, meanwhile, is going quite pale and trembly.<br><br>\"Mike, shut the hell up,\" snaps Bella.  \"Jesus.\"<br><br>\"Don't tell me to shut up!\" bristles Mike.<br><br>\"You're telling an abuse victim he <em>deserved it</em>, you have officially thrown polite discourse out a fortieth-story window and watched it go <em>splat</em> -\"<br><br>\"Yeah, Mike,\" says Jessica unexpectedly.  \"Just - shush, okay?  Go sit with Bill or somebody.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-01 06:08:00", reply_order: 17 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "Alice shrugs and takes another cookie, a cute little gingerbread heart.<br><br>It cracks in half in his hand.<br><br>He didn't think he was that upset, but it turns out that he in fact was.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 06:12:00", reply_order: 18 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "Mike doesn't seem inclined to go.  But for the moment he is out of things to say.<br><br>Bella splits her paper plate, dumps the cookies onto the clean bottom half to be devoured, picks up the Tupperware, and puts her hand on Alice's elbow and steers him away to another corner of the cafeteria.  She bought lunch today; given that she's full enough, she can leave everything and Angela will probably get it for her if no one else does.  \"I do not know what is wrong with him,\" she murmurs.  \"Here.\"  There's an empty couple of extra chairs, not associated with a table, in the corner.  She sits him down.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 105, created_at: "2012-10-01 06:15:00", reply_order: 19 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"That guy is gonna grow up to hit his wife,\" Alice remarks as he sits. It's not a fully serious prediction, but it is a comment on what he has seen of Mike's personality. ", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 06:21:00", reply_order: 20 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "\"He has other characteristics, and his behavior at age seventeen isn't a life sentence, but I do worry you're right,\" Bella murmurs.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-01 06:22:00", reply_order: 21 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yup,\" says Alice. \"Whatever, though. He's a fuckup but he's his own fuckup.\"<br><br>And just like that, he still hurts but he is no longer angry about it. Mike is not his problem, even if Mike apparently wants to be.<br><br>He would kind of like to be petted, but he isn't going to ask; it seems like the kind of thing Bella might not want to be doing in the corner of the lunchroom.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 06:27:00", reply_order: 22 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "[Yeah, that wouldn't do anything to convince anyone that I'm not sleeping with you,] Bella says.  [It annoys me generally to have people believe falsehoods about me that I didn't put there on purpose.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 43, created_at: "2012-10-01 06:28:00", reply_order: 23 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "[Okay,] he says agreeably. [Think I'll blow off the rest of the day and go hang out in my lair. Tell Finch I said hi?]", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 06:32:00", reply_order: 24 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "[Will do.  You'll miss me triumphantly kicking ass at badminton, though.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 06:33:00", reply_order: 25 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "[Yep,] says Alice.<br><br>Which will be a pity! But right now he really wants to do something intensely sensual, and since he doesn't feel like getting someone to beat him up and probably couldn't find anyone to have sex with him, his lair is the best place to go for that.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 06:36:00", reply_order: 26 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "[Have fun.  I'm going to Bio,] Bella says.  She does pat him once on the head, when she stands up, like he's a support.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 06:37:00", reply_order: 27 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "[See ya,] he says, and off he goes, abandoning his box of cookies.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 14:01:00", reply_order: 28 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "Bella sighs and puts the tupperware in her backpack, and proceeds to class.<br><br>Bio goes by and she heads for gym.  Time to learn to play badminton and then play it like she was born for it.  \"Hi, Ms. Finch.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 20:57:00", reply_order: 29 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"Hi, Bella.\"<br><br>She doesn't even ask about their mutual friend.<br><br>\"Still feeling cured, I hope?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-01 20:59:00", reply_order: 30 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "\"Yup,\" Bella says brightly.  \"So how does badminton work?  It involve rackets, right?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 21:00:00", reply_order: 31 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yes it does,\" says Ms. Finch. \"Congratulations.\" She hands Bella a racket. \"Now let's see if we can add to that store of knowledge.\"<br><br>She provides a thorough and concise explanation of the rules, punctuated with occasional humour of that dry sarcastic kind she seems to like so much.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-01 21:05:00", reply_order: 32 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "Bella giggles where appropriate.  \"Sounds simple enough,\" she says.  \"Do we get assigned partners or do we pick them?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 21:08:00", reply_order: 33 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"You pick them,\" says Ms. Finch, \"unless that takes too long or involves too much adolescent politics. So far this class hasn't been too bad about teams, though.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-01 21:17:00", reply_order: 34 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "\"Okay.  I just haven't met many people in this class besides Alice - oh, he asked me to call him Alice awhile ago, it's kind of weird - and he's not showing up today, so I'm not sure who to go with,\" Bella shrugs.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-01 21:19:00", reply_order: 35 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"Alice,\" she repeats. \"Funny. Well, if you can't find a partner once class starts, make pitiful faces at me and I'll get you straightened out.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-01 21:28:00", reply_order: 36 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "\"Will do,\" Bella agrees.  She experimentally swings her racket a few times.  She spends a pentagon on general athleticism so she won't be terribly exhausted by suddenly adding cardio to her day, and one on skill at racket-based sports in general after discovering that \"all sports\" is too general.  She gets a birdie from the pile and starts tapping it up into the air, over and over.  \"Hee.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 21:31:00", reply_order: 37 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "Well, some people <em>are</em> naturally talented. Ms. Finch doesn't find Bella too suspicious, and she is shortly distracted by the arrival of the rest of the class, anyway.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-01 21:43:00", reply_order: 38 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "Bella partners with someone who she vaguely thinks might also be in Government with her and who doesn't seem to like badminton much.<br><br>Her partner doesn't have much to do.<br><br>Bella grins so hard her face hurts.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-01 21:44:00", reply_order: 39 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "It's always nice to see the kiddies having fun.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-01 21:49:00", reply_order: 40 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "After class, Bella has no reason to stick around; she puts her equipment away and runs off to call her dad to come get her.  (Her car should be fixed soon.  If only she'd thought to magic it fixed when it first broke - sure, magic was scarcer then, but it might have taken only a square -)", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 21:52:00", reply_order: 41 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "About half an hour later, Alice brainphones her from his lair.<br><br>[Hey, you home yet?]", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 21:59:00", reply_order: 42 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "[Yeah, Charlie just left,] Bella says.  [What are you up to?]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 22:00:00", reply_order: 43 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "Napping on the floor of his sewing room, or he was a minute ago.<br><br>It hasn't been a great afternoon. Parts of it were, but on the whole, no.<br><br>[Shit-all, pretty much. How much ass did you kick in gym?]", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-01 22:03:00", reply_order: 44 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "[Lots.  Finch didn't even seem suspicious.  You recovering okay?  Mike was pretty awful to you at lunch.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 22:05:00", reply_order: 45 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "[I'll be fine,] he says, tucking his hands behind his head and gazing up at the ceiling. [Still kinda feel like shit, but whatever. You wanna hang out?]", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 22:11:00", reply_order: 46 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "[Sure.  Be over in a few.]  Bella walks out, and once she's deep in the woods turns invisible and takes flight.  [If Mike sits at my table again I'm just going to get up and leave, I'm done with him.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 43, created_at: "2012-10-01 22:14:00", reply_order: 47 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "[Good plan,] says Alice.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 22:16:00", reply_order: 48 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "[Maybe social consequences will have an effect where arguing for human decency didn't.  Also it's less work.  I think I've settled on soccer,] Bella continues.  [The school has a team, the women's teams aren't as generally denigrated as, like, baseball ones, and we're doing it in like a week so I can \"learn\" it then.]  She flies through the rock and down the spiral staircase.  \"Halloooo!\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 22:18:00", reply_order: 49 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"Hi!\" he calls from his position on the floor of the sewing room. Then he gets up, walks through the broad arch to meet her at the bottom of the stairs, and hugs her.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-01 22:21:00", reply_order: 50 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "Bella hugs him back and pets his hair.  \"So have you put your sewing room to any use yet?\" she asks.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 22:22:00", reply_order: 51 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"Not yet,\" he says. \"Haven't figured out if I want to use a pentagon or not.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-10-01 22:24:00", reply_order: 52 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "\"I'd say not,\" Bella says.  \"If you care about the process, why wouldn't you learn it the usual way?  And if you care about the results, actually sewing is redundant - you can just wish clothes into existence.\"  She gestures at her wish-jeans.  She's worn no non-wish jeans since she learned she could do that.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 22:25:00", reply_order: 53 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"I love you,\" says Alice. \"You make so much more sense than me.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 22:38:00", reply_order: 54 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "\"Yes, yes I do,\" says Bella merrily, drifting over to the chair in the corner and plopping into it.  \"It's good that you know that.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 22:39:00", reply_order: 55 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "Alice contemplates joining her in the chair—there is technically room—and then sits on the floor in front of her instead.<br><br>\"It's kinda hard to miss.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-10-01 22:41:00", reply_order: 56 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "Bella pets him some more.  \"I mentioned to Finch that you asked me to call you Alice, by the way.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 22:41:00", reply_order: 57 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "He leans his head on her knee and relaxes under her hand.<br><br>\"Wonder if she'll pick up the habit.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-01 22:44:00", reply_order: 58 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "\"Dunno.  I guess she'll surprise us.  I downloaded some college applications today,\" she remarks.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 22:46:00", reply_order: 59 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"Cool. Which ones?\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 22:48:00", reply_order: 60 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "\"All the Ivies - I have preferences among them, but any I can get into this year is noticeably preferable to any that won't take me until next year if at all - and the public universities here and in Florida, since I could claim residency in either now that my mom and Phil moved to Jacksonville.  And MIT, because that's good in its own right and right near Harvard.  I might not send in applications for all of them; I'll have to take a second look at the requirements and the average test scores and stuff.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 22:54:00", reply_order: 61 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"All kindsa places we might end up,\" Alice says contemplatively. He likes the uncertainty of it.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 22:55:00", reply_order: 62 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "\"Enh, it's mostly concentrated in New England,\" Bella says.  \"It's possible I should throw in Stanford though.  Why can't all the useful people go to <em>one place</em>?\" she sighs.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 22:57:00", reply_order: 63 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"Where would be the fun in that? Anyway, betcha you'll find <em>enough</em> useful people, wherever you end up.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-01 22:59:00", reply_order: 64 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "\"It's not all about a critical mass of useful people - it's also bad to have any major useful-people gaps.  If I go to Harvard and then someone from Stanford with whom I have no mutual friends makes more money than God, I'm in trouble; if I go to Yale and someone from - from the University of Tokyo invents a proprietary technology that interacts badly with magic and I have no way to get in touch with them and influence that <em>nonmagically</em>, then I'm also in trouble.  But I can't be everywhere yet and the world is big.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:01:00", reply_order: 65 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"There's already lotsa people you don't know who have more money than God, though,\" says Alice.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:03:00", reply_order: 66 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "\"Yes, I know.  I hope to meet people who know their cousins' kids or something,\" Bella says.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:04:00", reply_order: 67 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"...You know my mom,\" he observes. \"And my mom knows a <em>lot</em> of rich people.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:06:00", reply_order: 68 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "\"That's potentially useful, yes, but does she have parties where I could sidle up to same and comment on the hors d'oeuvres and then say hey, have you heard about this project I'm helping to run?\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:08:00", reply_order: 69 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"Maybe! Who the fuck knows what she's gonna do now?\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:12:00", reply_order: 70 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "\"Fair enough,\" Bella laughs.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:13:00", reply_order: 71 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"You could always suggest it to her and see what happens.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:16:00", reply_order: 72 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "Bella nods.  \"Next time I see her.  How have things at the house been?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 43, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:17:00", reply_order: 73 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"Good! Man, I did <em>not</em> know how much fun life could be without that asshole in it.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:19:00", reply_order: 74 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "Bella grins.  \"Awesome.\"  Pause.  \"You remembered to call Hilary and tell her not to bother picking you up from school, right?\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:20:00", reply_order: 75 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yup! She said from here on out I might as well just call her when I <em>want</em> a ride.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:23:00", reply_order: 76 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "Bella snickers.  \"So are you going to just fly everywhere now?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:23:00", reply_order: 77 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"Why the fuck not?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:24:00", reply_order: 78 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "\"I'm starting to wonder if my car's a lost cause.  They've hung onto it for a long time now; they should have had time to get whatever parts they needed.  I'd fly everywhere too but eventually somebody would wonder why I didn't have a vehicle in the parking lot.  If it didn't rain so much here I'd get a motorcycle.  Maybe I'll do that if there's better weather where I go to college...\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:25:00", reply_order: 79 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"Sounds like fun,\" he says. By which he means it sounds hot.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:31:00", reply_order: 80 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "Bella finds that amusing.  \"I wonder,\" she says very deliberately, \"if I'd look nice in all the requisite leather.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:31:00", reply_order: 81 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"You really fucking would,\" says Alice, happily.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:32:00", reply_order: 82 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "She laughs.  \"Well, I wouldn't want to try it in this climate, but anywhere else... maybe this is an argument in favor of Stanford.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:33:00", reply_order: 83 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"Suddenly I really like Stanford. Where the fuck is Stanford, anyway?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:34:00", reply_order: 84 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "\"Palo Alto, California,\" Bella says.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:34:00", reply_order: 85 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"Cool. Good motorcycle weather?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:35:00", reply_order: 86 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "\"I think so.  Maybe a little warm for it in summer.  But I could go around not wearing a helmet and have plenty of wind in my hair.  Or make the leather magically breathable.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:36:00", reply_order: 87 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "\"I love how you <em>solve</em> things.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:38:00", reply_order: 88 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "\"So do I,\" says Bella smugly.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:39:00", reply_order: 89 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 3, content: "Awwwwww. He hugs her leg.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:40:00", reply_order: 90 },
  { post_id: 19, user_id: 2, content: "Bella laughs and goes on petting him.  \"You are a strange, strange creature, Alice.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-01 23:40:00", reply_order: 91 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "[Yup,] says Alice. [Mom let me. Hilary lent me the dress. I look <em>adorable</em>. And nobody's even beat me up for it yet.]<br><br>Sure enough, when he he walks into the lunchroom, he is wearing a cornflower blue summer dress that is totally unsuited to the weather but surprisingly suited to Alice. Whispers and giggles and surreptitious pointing follow him to the lunch line.<br><br>[Want me to sit with you, or no? I have actual gingerbread I actually baked, this time.] Alice showing up at lunch with wish-baking for Bella and/or her tablemates has kind of become a thing, irregular but more than occasional.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-02 00:18:00", reply_order: 0 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "[Dunno, do you want to put up with Jessica gawping at you and asking if you are 'a trans'?]", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-02 00:40:00", reply_order: 1 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "[That sounds hilarious,] he says, proceeds to her table, sits, and opens his Tupperware of Mystery to reveal a lot of slightly misshapen gingerbread.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-10-02 00:42:00", reply_order: 2 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "\"Why're you wearing a dress?\" Jessica asks without preamble.  But she takes a gingerbread, as do Angela and Ben and of course Bella.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 00:44:00", reply_order: 3 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "\"Why're you wearing that shirt?\" he asks in return, taking some gingerbread for himself. (It is delicious as hell, naturally.)", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 00:49:00", reply_order: 4 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "\"My sister borrowed my last other clean one,\" says Jessica, unimpressed.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 00:50:00", reply_order: 5 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "\"Felt like it,\" he says sunnily, and nibbles his gingerbread.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 00:50:00", reply_order: 6 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "\"But why would you feel like wearing a <em>dress</em>?  Are you a <em>trans</em>?\"<br><br>[I haven't wished myself precog powers yet,] says Bella dryly.  [I have just met Jessica.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 00:51:00", reply_order: 7 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "[I love you.]<br><br>\"What do you care?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-10-02 00:56:00", reply_order: 8 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "\"Because it's <em>weird</em>!\" Jessica opines.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 00:56:00", reply_order: 9 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "\"Keep wondering,\" says Alice. \"Maybe you'll figure it out.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-02 00:57:00", reply_order: 10 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "\"Well, I <em>guessed</em> that you're a <em>trans</em>, but you won't even answer a simple question,\" pouts Jessica.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 00:58:00", reply_order: 11 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "\"Okay, try this one on for size,\" says Alice, waving his gingerbread in a shrug-like gesture. \"It's <em>not</em> a simple question, and it's not gonna <em>be</em> a simple question until you stop thinking there's any good reason why I <em>shouldn't</em> feel like wearing a dress, and at that point you're probably gonna know the answer already.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 01:04:00", reply_order: 12 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "Jessica chews that over a bit.  \"I'm not a trans,\" she offers.  \"That's simple.  If you are one that should be simple, too.  And I don't think it's like illegal or anything?\"  She looks at Bella.<br><br>\"Not illegal,\" Bella confirms.<br><br>\"But it's weird!  You're a boy, unless you're a trans, so -\"<br><br>\"I think it might be 'transgender',\" Angela says softly.<br><br>\"Oh.  A transgender.  So it's weird for you to wear a dress and you must have a reason because the boys who don't have reasons don't do it,\" says Jessica.<br><br>[Well, that was surprisingly lucid,] comments Bella.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-02 01:06:00", reply_order: 13 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "[Yup. I'm surprised.]<br><br>\"Okay,\" he says, \"so what if the reason is that there's no reason not to?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-10-02 01:11:00", reply_order: 14 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "\"But there are reasons not to,\" Jessica says.  \"You might get beat up, and also that looks really cold for February, and also everyone will think it's weird, and ask you why you're doing it, and also it doesn't fit you very well!\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 01:12:00", reply_order: 15 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "\"Don't care,\" he says, \"don't care, don't care, don't care, and wrong.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-02 01:15:00", reply_order: 16 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "\"Well, why don't you care?\" Jessica demands.  \"And it - well, there's no such thing as a dress fitting on a guy, anyway.\"  She starts to reexamine the fit before apparently deciding that would look uncomfortably like she was checking him out and breaking eye contact.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 01:16:00", reply_order: 17 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "\"Okay,\" says Alice, \"I'm taking that as a challenge. And do you <em>really</em> need to ask me why I don't care if I get beat up?\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 01:19:00", reply_order: 18 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "\"Well, it doesn't make sense - I know you don't care, but I don't know why,\" Jessica says.  \"Why won't you just tell us if you're a trans or - a transgender or not?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 01:20:00", reply_order: 19 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "He takes a bite of his gingerbread. [Bella, help me out here. How do I make this stupid question not stupid so I can answer it?]", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 01:22:00", reply_order: 20 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "[Well, geez, <em>I'm</em> not clear on what you get out of wearing dresses and I can read your <em>mind</em>.  If there's an answer you haven't been thinking of it while I've been looking.]", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-02 01:23:00", reply_order: 21 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "[So read me?] he says.<br><br>The problem: he likes guy stuff and girl stuff, perhaps not equally, but <em>both</em>-ly. So if he says he's 'a trans' (Jessica's terminology doesn't bug him, except inasmuch as it is distractingly hilarious), that's wrong, but if he says he's <em>not</em>, that's <em>also</em> wrong. He's not a boy, but he's not a girl. Or he is a boy, and he is a girl. From where he's standing he can't really tell the difference.<br><br>Also, he just really likes dresses. He thinks they look cute on him. And he is totally going to make one that fits him perfectly, just to show Jessica what that looks like.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-10-02 01:29:00", reply_order: 22 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "[So you're a mutant gender on top of everything else.  Why am I not astonished?] Bella says.  [Tell Jessica you're, I dunno, half-trans or something.  I don't know why dresses are even a girl thing, they're awkward and impractical.  I will go on wearing jeans or maybe motorcycle leather even after I take over the world and start affecting the use of crowns.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 01:34:00", reply_order: 23 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "[Thank you for making me think about you in motorcycle leather again,] Alice says cheerfully. [You're the best.]<br><br>The crown adds a certain something to the mental image, too.<br><br>\"How about half,\" he suggests to Jessica. \"Half trans.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 01:37:00", reply_order: 24 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "Jessica makes a series of thoughtful faces.  \"Is that a thing?\"<br><br>\"Apparently,\" Bella says.  [No problem.]", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-02 01:38:00", reply_order: 25 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "\"It is now,\" says Alice.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-02 01:41:00", reply_order: 26 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "\"Well, okay, that was all you had to say,\" says Jessica huffily.  \"Honestly.\"<br><br>Bella rolls her eyes.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-02 01:43:00", reply_order: 27 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "\"Not sorry,\" says Alice, serenely.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 01:44:00", reply_order: 28 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "\"You need to work on your social skills,\" Jessica advises him.<br><br>\"Thank you for the gingerbread,\" Angela puts in desperately, hoping to change the subject.  \"It's delicious.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 01:45:00", reply_order: 29 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "He grins at Angela. \"You're welcome. Made it myself.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 01:48:00", reply_order: 30 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "\"What's in it?\" Angela's boyfriend asks helpfully.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 01:48:00", reply_order: 31 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "Alice rattles off a list of ingredients, many of which sound quite tasty on their own.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-02 01:49:00", reply_order: 32 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "Eventually lunch ends.  [Are you going to come to gym today?] Bella asks as she heads for bio.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:00:00", reply_order: 33 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "[Yep.]", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:03:00", reply_order: 34 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "[Cool.]<br><br>Gym arrives.  The badminton nets are gone, and there is a soccer ball prominently located in the gym.<br><br>\"This is the game with the kicking, right?\" Bella asks Ms. Finch, winking.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:05:00", reply_order: 35 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "\"You don't have to look so eager,\" says Ms. Finch, laughing. \"Yes, this is the game with the kicking. I'd specify what exactly you'll be kicking, but then you might wink at me again.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:08:00", reply_order: 36 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "\"What are the rules exactly?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:09:00", reply_order: 37 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "Ms. Finch gives her the rundown. Halfway through, Alice shows up.<br><br>\"Nice of you to join us, Wonderland. Will you be wearing that for soccer?\"<br><br>Alice twirls.<br><br>\"I'll take that as a yes,\" she says, and goes right back to explaining the game to Bella.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:11:00", reply_order: 38 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "Bella listens attentively.  It sounds pretty fun.  She decides to wait for about a minute into the class before pentagoning this one.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:13:00", reply_order: 39 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "Perhaps surprisingly, no one bothers Alice about his choice of gym clothes. Class proceeds. Alice has a blast.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:15:00", reply_order: 40 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "Bella shows off.  (But she makes sure to display virtues of teamwork, where applicable - she does not make ridiculous trick shots just because she can, when there's a teammate right there to pass to.)", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:16:00", reply_order: 41 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "At the end of class, Ms. Finch approaches Bella.<br><br>\"You are suspiciously good at this game,\" she says. \"And I mean that in the best possible way.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:17:00", reply_order: 42 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "\"It's fun!\" Bella says.  \"I'm usually good at things I like, it was just never safe to apply it to sports before recently.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:18:00", reply_order: 43 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "\"Wanna join a team?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:22:00", reply_order: 44 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "\"I would!\" Bella says happily.  \"When is that?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:23:00", reply_order: 45 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "Ms. Finch grins.<br><br>\"Tryouts start today and go through the week,\" she says. \"Despite rumour, I have never thrown a failed candidate into the scorpion pit.\"<br><br>\"What about the ones who don't fail?\" wonders Alice.<br><br>\"I need those.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:31:00", reply_order: 46 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "\"Cool, I'll just stay after today then,\" Bella says.  \"How often are practices?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:32:00", reply_order: 47 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "\"Tuesday Thursday Monday Wednesday Friday repeat,\" says Ms. Finch cheerfully, \"because I hate you and want you to suffer.\"<br><br>Alice giggles.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:35:00", reply_order: 48 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "Bella giggles.  \"It's a good thing I don't have any other extracurriculars lined up.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:37:00", reply_order: 49 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "\"Lucky you,\" Ms. Finch agrees.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:37:00", reply_order: 50 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "[Although I wonder if I should take up an instrument just to be really well-rounded.  I could claim I bought it when I was fourteen and never practiced when whichever parent was home out of politeness; I think that one I'll need more backstory than \"turns out I'm naturally talented\".  What do you think, flute?  Those are easy to hide.]<br><br>\"Cool,\" Bella says.  \"So I'll just stick around I guess.\"  She scoops up the ball onto her toe and starts kneeing it back and forth, left and right.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:40:00", reply_order: 51 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "Alice parks himself on a bench, leaning forward with his elbows on his knees. [Flute sounds cool. Mmm, or clarinet. Clarinets are sexy.]<br><br>\"Do us all a favour and sit like a girl, Wonderland,\" says Ms. Finch. \"No one here wants to see up that skirt.\"<br><br>Laughing, he crosses his legs. \"Better?\"<br><br>\"Much.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:44:00", reply_order: 52 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "[I'm going to make it flute.  Not a big clarinet fan.]  \"If he tries out for soccer, which team would you put him on?\" Bella teases aloud.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:47:00", reply_order: 53 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "\"You couldn't pay me to put that kid on a team of any kind,\" says Ms. Finch. Alice beams, flattered.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:48:00", reply_order: 54 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "Bella laughs.<br><br>She's been laughing a lot in recent weeks.  She likes this.  \"What do we do in tryouts?\" she inquires.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:50:00", reply_order: 55 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "\"You try,\" says Ms. Finch, dryly.<br><br>Alice laughs.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:51:00", reply_order: 56 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 2, content: "Bella does, when everyone else there to try out arrives, and again shows off (within believable talented-highschooler range; she'll save major ridiculousness for when scouts swing by, if they ever do).<br><br>Afterwards, she calls her dad - who is confused about why she didn't call an hour earlier - and goes home to add to all her applications that she plays flute and soccer.  Then she submits them all, and conjures a flute and pentagons ability to operate it - and amuses herself playing it all the rest of the afternoon.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:52:00", reply_order: 57 },
  { post_id: 20, user_id: 3, content: "Alice amuses himself listening.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 02:58:00", reply_order: 58 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "[Sure!] he says cheerfully. [What kind and when?]", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-10-02 03:23:00", reply_order: 0 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "[Custom one just now.  Come over and watch me conjure it up,] Bella says cheerily.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-02 03:24:00", reply_order: 1 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "[Fuck yes!]<br><br>He turns invisible and zooms up out of his lair.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 03:27:00", reply_order: 2 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "When he arrives, Bella's standing in the garage; it doesn't have room for a car - Charlie parks on the street and Bella used to park in the driveway before her station wagon got busted.  But it has room for a motorcycle.<br><br>She's had a while to design it now, and what she doesn't know about motorcycle functionality she can let the magic handle.  \"Behold,\" she intones, and burns a pentagon.<br><br>It appears.<br><br>It's sleek and beetle-black and detailed in brilliant gold with patterns like thin vines twining around all its edges.  If it were an inch long and strung on a chain it'd be jewelry; instead it's like a metallic animal crouched on the floor of the garage.<br><br>\"Doesn't need gas,\" Bella brags.  \"Can use it in case someone's watching me though.\"<br><br>She wishes on another pentagon, because she wants her riding gear (pants, jacket, fingerless gloves, and a pair of short-heeled half-calf boots) to have certain properties.  \"Repels water, helpfully temperature-regulating whether warm or cold,\" she says.  There's a helmet too, appearing in the same conjuration, equally shiny, although whether she'll use it or it's just for show is anyone's guess.<br><br>It's black with gold designs on it too, and it fits like a sexy, sexy glove.<br><br>\"After you went and got me such a silly present I just had to go ahead and get my motorcycle license,\" she shrugs, petting the soft leather on her thigh.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 03:36:00", reply_order: 3 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "\"...I don't know who I want to fuck more, you or the bike,\" says a stunned and delighted Alice.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-10-02 03:38:00", reply_order: 4 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "Bella bursts out laughing.  \"Please don't fuck my bike.  But I thought you might approve, yes.  So this <em>is</em> the kind of thing you might randomly decide to spend a fraction of your damages on.\"<br><br>She tilts her head.  \"There might be extra requirements to drive a motorcycle at my age, actually.  My birthday's not till September...  I wonder if I need Charlie's permission or something.  I will look into that.\"  She strokes her bike.  \"But I'm keeping this regardless.  I like it.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-02 03:42:00", reply_order: 5 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "\"I promise not to fuck your bike,\" says Alice.<br><br>He does not promise not to go home later and <em>think</em> about fucking it. Mmmmmm.<br><br>(Promising something doesn't mean the same thing to him that it does to most people. The <em>promise</em>, by itself, is meaningless. What he's saying, the thought behind the words, is that he acknowledges she doesn't want him to do that and therefore predicts that he won't. He isn't paying much attention to this definition at the moment, but it's still there.)<br><br>\"And I am glad that you are keeping it, because it's fucking awesome and so are you.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-10-02 03:45:00", reply_order: 6 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "Bella grins.  \"Now I have to find out if I can get licensed to use this thing in time to drive myself to the airport so I can go interview at Stanford.  You'd think I'd be nervous about leaving it at an airport, but it won't start or even roll if anyone but me tries and when not operating it's way too heavy to lift.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-02 03:52:00", reply_order: 7 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "\"...A motorbike this sexy that's also unstealable is gonna get noticed,\" Alice points out.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 03:54:00", reply_order: 8 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "\"What, just because there's a bit of a trick to the ignition, the wheels lock up when it's turned off, and it weighs several hundred pounds?\" Bella says.  \"It might get keyed, but I can fix that.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 03:55:00", reply_order: 9 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "\"Mm,\" says Alice. \"Guess it's not that likely that somebody <em>really</em> determined is gonna try.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 03:57:00", reply_order: 10 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "Bella nods.  \"I mean, I guess I could also put an alarm on it, but no one pays attention to those.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 03:58:00", reply_order: 11 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "\"The only thing a car alarm <em>ever does</em> is annoy the fuck out of people,\" Alice asserts.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-10-02 03:59:00", reply_order: 12 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "\"Right.  They were a significant component of making that poor defense lawyer lose so much sleep,\" Bella says sweetly.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:00:00", reply_order: 13 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "...Alice cracks up.<br><br>[I love you,] he says by brainphone, because he is laughing too hard to use out-loud words.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:02:00", reply_order: 14 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "\"I'm gonna go look up what I have to do to be licensed to use my silly, excessive present that I cannot sensibly return because you had it made custom for me,\" Bella says, heading into the house after petting her bike one more time.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:07:00", reply_order: 15 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "Alice gives the bike one last lingering look, and then follows her. That thing is <em>gorgeous</em>. And it suits her perfectly. He wishes he could actually get her a present that cool. But it's pretty much guaranteed that anything he might think to provide is inferior to what she could wish up for herself.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:10:00", reply_order: 16 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "\"You're covering for me.  I can't get that for myself, not readily,\" Bella responds to this thought.  \"You as good as got me this, because otherwise I'd have to fabricate the plausible ability to build the damn thing in order to have it in public.  Oh, and you got it for me from a super secretive private hobbyist you met on the Internet who did you a one-time favor and who does not want his or her name publicized.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:13:00", reply_order: 17 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "\"Cool,\" he says, and starts inventing hilariously implausible lies to cover for this imaginary person, because that is what he would actually do in that case.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:15:00", reply_order: 18 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "Bella looks up motorcycle laws in Washington.  It turns out she needs Charlie's permission to take a sixteen-hour course and then pass a written test to be allowed to bike hither and thither.  \"Sixteen hours, dang,\" she says.  \"Oh well.  If it turns out it would help, can I borrow some cash to pay an instructor to let me do that over a weekend instead of sitting through some regularly scheduled class that meets for an hour every evening for two and a half weeks?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:20:00", reply_order: 19 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yup,\" says Alice.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:21:00", reply_order: 20 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "\"Grand.  If you care, I'll pay you back when I too become a millionaire.  If you don't, I will forget about it altogether after about twelve minutes of mild guilt.\"  She starts looking for motorcycle instructors.  She can just fly wherever, land a few blocks away, and claim to have gotten a ride.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:22:00", reply_order: 21 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "\"I so don't care,\" he says. \"Oh, uh, people are <em>really</em> gonna think we're fucking if you show up to school on that thing. You cool with that?\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:23:00", reply_order: 22 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "\"Meh,\" says Bella.  \"Don't care enough to <em>not use it</em>.  I will carry on denying it and say you're just buying me things with your court-awarded money because I helped you with the trial stuff.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:26:00", reply_order: 23 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "\"Okay, cool.\"<br><br>A few things click in his head. Presents; beautiful things; designing for function and form.<br><br>\"Hey, can I make you hot clothes?\" he asks, already running through possibilities in his head. Dresses, various lengths; suits; assorted other items.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:30:00", reply_order: 24 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "\"Not a fan of dresses or suits on me in general, although if I have to show up to something super-formal I'd wear a dress.  Maybe now that I don't trip on imaginary things all the time I'll start showing up to dances?  I'd wear dresses to those, and I'll let you make 'em if you want if you let me vet the design.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:34:00", reply_order: 25 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "\"You got it.\"<br><br><em>Dancing</em>. Oh, he can definitely design dresses for dancing.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:37:00", reply_order: 26 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "Bella grins.  \"Spiffy.  I wonder if dancing is one pentagon, or one per type?\"  She tries it.  \"Huh.  Works with one, but I probably couldn't win a waltz contest, I think this is just general I-can-dance-now.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:40:00", reply_order: 27 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "\"...Wanna dance?\" he suggests, grinning. Because why not?", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:42:00", reply_order: 28 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "\"D'you know how?\" Bella asks.  \"Yet?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:43:00", reply_order: 29 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "He shrugs and burns a pentagon.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:44:00", reply_order: 30 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "Bella can see it disappear.  She shrugs and puts some waltz music on, and leads, even though he's taller and she's a girl.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:45:00", reply_order: 31 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "That is because Bella is <em>perfect</em>.<br><br>Completely for the fuck of it, Alice wishes himself a magnificently twirly pleated skirt.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:48:00", reply_order: 32 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "Bella laughs, and twirls him accordingly.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:48:00", reply_order: 33 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "He loves her <em>so much</em>.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:49:00", reply_order: 34 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "Bella doesn't get tired at this level of physical activity for hours.  She can dance as long as she wants.  But the music ends eventually and she spins Alice into a closing dip.<br><br>\"That was fun,\" she says.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:52:00", reply_order: 35 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "\"Whee!\" says Alice, sitting down on the floor.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:53:00", reply_order: 36 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "\"I love being magical,\" crows Bella.  \"I love it <em>lots</em>.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:55:00", reply_order: 37 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "\"I love it too. And I love you being magical. And I love you,\" Alice recites happily.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:56:00", reply_order: 38 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "\"Charlie'll be home in under an hour,\" she says, glancing at the clock.  \"Time to start dinner.  You staying?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:57:00", reply_order: 39 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yep,\" he says, smoothing out his skirt.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 04:58:00", reply_order: 40 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "\"I'm kinda impressed with Charlie for not having remarked on your new clothes,\" Bella says, heading down the stairs and starting on some rice to serve with fried fish.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 05:02:00", reply_order: 41 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "\"Me too,\" he says, laughing.<br><br>Once again Charlie defies Alice's experience of dads! That is a good thing. He should keep doing that.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-10-02 05:04:00", reply_order: 42 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "Bella cooks.  She hands Alice things to stir, and stale bread to turn into crumbs.  Charlie's home on time, remarks neither on Alice's presence nor on his attire, and is loudly appreciative of the food.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 05:17:00", reply_order: 43 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "Alice is <em>also</em> loudly appreciative of the food, although half of his remarks thereon are technically silent.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-10-02 05:29:00", reply_order: 44 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "\"So Dad,\" says Bella.  \"Alice got me a ridiculous present, and I can't return it because he went and got it <em>custom</em> and anyway I really like it.  So... um...\"<br><br>\"Mm?\" Charlie asks.  \"Why would you return it if you like it?\"<br><br>\"Well, I'm not licensed to drive it,\" says Bella.<br><br>Charlie's silent for a beat.  \"Laney, did you get my daughter a motorcycle?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 05:34:00", reply_order: 45 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yup,\" says Alice, sunnily.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 05:38:00", reply_order: 46 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "\"It's <em>gorgeous</em>, Dad, and I'd be safe, because - y'know - and I was thinking I could drive myself to the airport so I can fly to California to get interviewed by Stanford...\"<br><br>Charlie blinks.<br><br>\"Stanford?\"<br><br>\"Yeah, they want an interview!\" Bella says sunnily.  \"I can fly down on a weekend, and you won't have to drive me... if I can get your permission to take a motorcycle course.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 05:39:00", reply_order: 47 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "Alice beams. Bella is just delightful, okay?", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-02 05:40:00", reply_order: 48 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "Charlie hems and haws.  \"Well,\" he says finally.  \"If you're sure you'll be safe?\"<br><br>\"Quite sure,\" Bella says.<br><br>\"Well, fine, if you need my permission I suppose you've got it.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 05:50:00", reply_order: 49 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "Alice continues to beam! He is thinking about Bella on her motorcycle. They are pleasant thoughts.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-02 05:53:00", reply_order: 50 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "\"Wanna see the bike, Dad?\" Bella asks when the food has all been tucked away into various tummies.<br><br>\"Sure,\" Charlie says.<br><br>So she takes him out to see the bike.<br><br>\"Damn,\" he says.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-02 05:55:00", reply_order: 51 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yup,\" says Alice.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-10-02 05:57:00", reply_order: 52 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 2, content: "\"Yes, you may learn to drive that,\" Charlie repeats.<br><br>Bella grins.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-02 05:59:00", reply_order: 53 },
  { post_id: 21, user_id: 3, content: "Alice twirls joyously.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-10-02 06:00:00", reply_order: 54 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 3, content: "[Toldja!]<br><br>For once, he is in the stupidly huge house instead of his lair, baking cookies with Hilary.<br><br>[Wanna come over and eat cookies and brag?]", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-04 02:45:00", reply_order: 0 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 2, content: "[That sounds awesome.]  Bella puts on her riding gear, hops onto Tegu, and purrs towards the stupidly huge house.  She is perfectly comfortable even in the rain, because she thought of that ahead of time.  She is pleased with herself.  [What kinda cookies?]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-04 02:46:00", reply_order: 1 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 3, content: "[Oreo cheesecake cookies! They look tasty as fuck.]", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-04 02:48:00", reply_order: 2 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 2, content: "[Mmm.]<br><br>Tegu's fast.  She speeds a little.  [Anything else going on?]", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-04 02:49:00", reply_order: 3 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 3, content: "[Nah. It's pretty much cookies.]", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-10-04 02:54:00", reply_order: 4 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 2, content: "[That's sufficient excuse,] Bella says contently.<br><br>After a few minutes, she parks her bike in front of the house.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-04 02:57:00", reply_order: 5 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 3, content: "The sound of her pulling up is not audible from the kitchen, so she'll have to ring the doorbell like anybody else.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:02:00", reply_order: 6 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 2, content: "And she does.  <em>Ding!</em>", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:03:00", reply_order: 7 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 3, content: "\"Who on earth is that?\" wonders Hilary.<br><br>\"Couldn't tell ya,\" says Alice. \"Want me to get it?\"<br><br>\"Sure, go on.\"<br><br>Shortly thereafter, Alice opens the door.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:04:00", reply_order: 8 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 2, content: "\"Hallo!\" Bella says brightly.  \"I got into Stanford!\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:05:00", reply_order: 9 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 3, content: "He doesn't know he's going to do it until he does, but what he does is in fact give her a hug that lifts her right off the floor.<br><br>\"Awesome!\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:07:00", reply_order: 10 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 2, content: "\"Eep!  Yes, yes it is,\" laughs Bella.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:08:00", reply_order: 11 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 3, content: "He puts her down. Then he hugs her again.<br><br>\"What's the occasion?\" inquires Hilary from down the hall. Alice judges that this is Bella's moment to brag some more.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:10:00", reply_order: 12 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 2, content: "\"I'm going to Stanford in the fall,\" Bella trills.  She thought she was loud enough to be heard in the kitchen - that's why she bothered to repeat herself aloud even to Alice - but she doesn't mind saying it again.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:12:00", reply_order: 13 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 3, content: "\"That definitely sounds like a hug moment,\" says Hilary, and holds out her arms.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:13:00", reply_order: 14 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 2, content: "Bella hugs her too.  \"I'm very excited,\" she agrees.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:15:00", reply_order: 15 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 3, content: "Hilary grins.<br><br>\"Well, lucky for you, we've got a beautiful batch of cookies in the oven which I now officially rededicate to the cause of celebrating Bella Swan's Stanford acceptance.\"<br><br>Alice applauds.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:16:00", reply_order: 16 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 2, content: "\"Oooh, my very own celebratory cookies,\" exclaims Bella happily.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:17:00", reply_order: 17 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 3, content: "\"Well, I hope you'll share,\" Hilary teases.<br><br>\"She'd better,\" says Alice, glancing at her as though to judge the capacity of her stomach. \"I think if she tried to eat all those by herself she'd explode.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:24:00", reply_order: 18 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 2, content: "\"I bet I could do it if I really wanted,\" Bella sniffs.  \"But I'll share anyway.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:25:00", reply_order: 19 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 3, content: "\"Generous of you,\" says Hilary.<br><br>\"Well, she did get into <em>Stan</em>ford,\" says Alice.<br><br>\"Do I detect a hint of envy?\" asks Hilary.<br><br>\"Nope,\" says Alice.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:32:00", reply_order: 20 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 2, content: "Bella snickers.  \"What manner of celebratory cookies am I sharing?\" she asks.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:35:00", reply_order: 21 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 3, content: "\"Oreo cheesecake!\" says Hilary. Alice beams.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:43:00", reply_order: 22 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 2, content: "\"Tomorrow I'm going to read the entire course catalog,\" Bella says.  \"It's long.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:44:00", reply_order: 23 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 3, content: "\"Have fun with that,\" says Alice.<br><br>\"Sounds thrilling,\" Hilary agrees.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:45:00", reply_order: 24 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 2, content: "Eventually cookies are de-ovened, and cooled, and eaten.  \"Mmmm.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:46:00", reply_order: 25 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 3, content: "\"Do I smell baking?\" asks a voice from just outside the kitchen.<br><br>\"Yes you do!\" says Hilary. \"We're celebrating!\"<br><br>\"What are you—oh. Hello, Bella,\" says Judith as she steps inside.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:49:00", reply_order: 26 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 2, content: "\"Hello,\" Bella says.  She's not sure what she should be calling Judith now, but she can get away with not knowing for a while.  \"We're celebrating me getting into Stanford.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:55:00", reply_order: 27 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 3, content: "\"Oh,\" she repeats. \"Congratulations!\"<br><br>Entirely sincere, and entirely without thought of contrasting this accomplishment against her delinquent son's dwindling likelihood of ever graduating high school. Alice smiles.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:56:00", reply_order: 28 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 2, content: "\"Thanks!  I'm excited.  I'm going to join the soccer team and the orchestra, and maybe if the practice times don't conflict I'll try out for some plays or something, and of course there's classes.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-04 03:58:00", reply_order: 29 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 3, content: "\"That does sound like a lot,\" Judith says vaguely. Alice hands her a cookie just to give her something to do other than ramble.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-04 04:07:00", reply_order: 30 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 2, content: "\"I'm going to be busy,\" Bella agrees.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-04 04:08:00", reply_order: 31 },
  { post_id: 23, user_id: 3, content: "\"Busy being awesome,\" says Alice.<br><br>\"Yes, I think that's clear,\" says Judith, and smiles.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-10-04 04:14:00", reply_order: 32 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "The morning of the day that he is allowed to officially show up, Alice has an <em>idea</em>.<br><br>He spends the rest of that morning immersed in clothing design.<br><br>At last, a few hours past lunch, he twirls in front of the full-length mirror in his sewing room. Layers and layers of long, pointed fabric petals flutter with the movement; delicate, glittering fabric wings quiver behind his back.<br><br>That seems likely to make about the right first impression.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-11 04:49:00", reply_order: 0 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "[You're very silly,] Bella tells him.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-11 04:51:00", reply_order: 1 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "[Yep!] he says brightly, and picks up the package containing Janine's dress, and invisibles his way through the magic door, and de-invisibles when he is sure no one is in the stairwell to see him, and takes the stairs up to Bella's floor.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-11 04:54:00", reply_order: 2 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "Bella waits for him to actually knock before she gets the door.  She wants to be that helpful girl who is super-competent and has useful connections - not that girl who might possibly be psychic.<br><br>\"Hi!\" she says, greeting him with a hug.  She avoids messing up his wings in so doing.  \"Alice, this is Janine.  Janine, this is my boyfriend.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 04:55:00", reply_order: 3 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "\"Hi!\" He hugs back cheerfully, then turns to Janine and holds out the neatly tissue-wrapped package. \"Gotcha something,\" he says with a wink.<br><br>\"Hello it is nice to meet you <em>is that my dress</em>,\" says Janine, yoinking the package out of his hand and tearing it open.<br><br>It is, indeed, her dress: sky-blue, demurely high-necked and low-hemmed, with elbow-length sleeves and slightly puffed shoulders and a faint pattern in the fabric that hints at clouds.<br><br>\"It's <em>perfect</em>,\" she gushes, hugging it to her. \"Thank you thank you! I will pay you, just a moment.\" She lays the dress down carefully on her bed and digs out her wallet.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-10-11 05:08:00", reply_order: 4 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "\"Looks like something a Disney princess would wear,\" comments Bella.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 05:10:00", reply_order: 5 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yes it does!\" says Janine. \"It is delightful!\"<br><br>She counts out five twenties and hands them to Alice, who shrugs and hands them to Bella.<br><br>\"No pockets on this thing,\" he says, tugging at the skirt of his fairy tunic. \"Guess I shoulda thought of that.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-10-11 05:13:00", reply_order: 6 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "\"No worries,\" says Bella, tucking them into her purse.  She makes a small point of putting them in a separate pocket from her main cash stash in the unlikely event that Janine is paying attention.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 05:14:00", reply_order: 7 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "Janine is busy asking Alice, \"What should I call you?\"<br><br>\"Whatever you feel like,\" he says.<br><br>\"Tinkerbell?\" she giggles.<br><br>\"Knock yourself out.\"<br><br>\"I think I'll stick with Alice,\" says Janine.<br><br>\"Go for it.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-10-11 05:16:00", reply_order: 8 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "This exchange makes Bella snicker.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 05:18:00", reply_order: 9 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "Alice grins at her. So, tentatively, does Janine.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-11 05:19:00", reply_order: 10 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "\"What should I tell the other four wanters of dresses about when they should expect 'em?\" Bella asks.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 05:20:00", reply_order: 11 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "\"Not yet,\" he says. \"Soonish. I'll probably be done one this week but I don't know which one.\"<br><br>\"You're so precise,\" Janine observes, and Alice laughs good-naturedly.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-11 05:22:00", reply_order: 12 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "\"All right,\" Bella says.  \"What's the Disney Princess dress made of?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 05:25:00", reply_order: 13 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "\"Cotton,\" says Alice. Janine nods approvingly.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-10-11 05:31:00", reply_order: 14 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "\"An excellent plant,\" Bella says.  \"Alice, anything you wanna see while you're here?\"  [And light bounces off of you?]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 05:32:00", reply_order: 15 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "Alice giggles.<br><br>\"Dunno, like what?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-11 05:33:00", reply_order: 16 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "Bella shrugs.  \"Parts of campus.  The downtown area.  There's stuff in Palo Alto too, if we go there.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-11 05:34:00", reply_order: 17 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "\"Sure,\" he says. \"Show me someplace cool.\" [That I haven't been already.]", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-11 14:31:00", reply_order: 18 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "\"There's a plant nursery,\" Bella suggests, \"if you don't mind sitting behind me on Tegu to get there.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 20:04:00", reply_order: 19 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "\"I so don't.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-10-11 20:08:00", reply_order: 20 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "\"Yeah,\" says Bella, smirking.  \"I didn't think that was gonna be a problem.\"  She heads into the closet for her leather ensemble, which goes on over her regular clothes.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-11 20:08:00", reply_order: 21 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "Alice admires her openly.<br><br>Janine clearly thinks they are both adorable.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-10-11 20:11:00", reply_order: 22 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "In short order Bella is jacketed and leather-pantsed and booted and gloved; her helmet is sitting on Tegu.  \"Off we go,\" she says, and she trots out the door.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 20:12:00", reply_order: 23 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "\"Have fun, guys!\" says Janine. Alice waves to her on his way out, and she waves back.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-11 20:15:00", reply_order: 24 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "Bella conjures an extra helmet in the stairwell - [You left yours on Tegu, you have one because of course you don't usually get around by flying,] she coaches - and they go out to her bike.  She zooms them along to the garden, which is indeed full of interesting plants, including cactuses and other things unheard of in Forks.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 20:17:00", reply_order: 25 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "The interesting plants are fun and so is Bella. Alice is fond of both.<br><br>At some point, a thought occurs to him: [Should <em>I</em> get a bike?]", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-11 20:19:00", reply_order: 26 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "[Quite possibly.  Want me to design you one?]", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-11 20:22:00", reply_order: 27 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "He <em>beams</em>. [Yes!]", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-11 20:24:00", reply_order: 28 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "Bella starts thinking about that.  [Any guidelines I should bear in mind?]", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-11 20:25:00", reply_order: 29 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "[Mm... dunno,] he says, and starts thinking of vague mental images. He kind of likes that thing his wishcoins do, where they're flat glossy black unless you see them out of the corner of your eye, and then all of a sudden there's colours. Possibly that is too magical to use for a pretending-to-be-normal bike, though.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-11 20:32:00", reply_order: 30 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "[A little bit.  I was thinking a bolder color scheme for you anyway.  If I mess with the finish it could look different colors from different angles?  Not traditional but hardly magical; they do it for advertisements, something to do with ridges on the surface.]", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-11 20:35:00", reply_order: 31 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "[<em>Awesome</em>,] says Alice.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-10-11 20:37:00", reply_order: 32 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "['Kay,] says Bella merrily.  [There's also the question of where I should appear it.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 20:41:00", reply_order: 33 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "[Not a clue,] says Alice.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-11 20:41:00", reply_order: 34 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "[I guess I could door back to Forks invisible, and pop it into your garage, and you can say your mysterious internet motorcycle supplier delivered it when no one was watching.]<br><br>The design's forming up in her head.  Pretty bike.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 20:42:00", reply_order: 35 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "[Works for me,] he says serenely.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-11 20:51:00", reply_order: 36 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "[We can go when we're through looking at this pretty garden.]<br><br>They finish looking at the pretty garden in due course, and then hop on Tegu back towards school, and duck into the door into Alice's basement when no one is looking. Janine, even if she sees Tegu, will probably just think they slipped off somewhere to make out. (Which might also wind up being true.)", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 20:51:00", reply_order: 37 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "Alice's lair and its magic doors are so convenient!<br><br>Alice has no need to be invisible in his own home when no one actually knows for sure that he isn't in it; he leads invisi-Bella up out of the basement and out to the garage.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-11 20:53:00", reply_order: 38 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "In the garage - which is unoccupied - she creates him a bike.<br><br>The exposed piping is all black and arranged to look like it's got a rainbow sheen of oil over selected parts.  Seen from the front, the surfaces - not those underportions but the carapace - look brilliantly red, fading pinker towards each edge, like someone shot the bike in the middle of each panel and it bled very carefully.  Seen from the back, it looks blue fading to sky-cyan, and viewed directly from the side both colors muddle to purple-lavender.  It's bulkier than Tegu, it looks more like a spaceship than a cat, but it's low to the ground and glimmers with every saccade of the eye.<br><br>[Ta-da!]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 20:58:00", reply_order: 39 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "He marvels at it for a moment.<br><br>Then he says, [Can I have sex with <em>this</em> one?]", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-10-11 21:01:00", reply_order: 40 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "[It <em>is</em> yours,] Bella says.  [I'm not gonna supervise if you do, so warn me if I'm reading you when you take it into your head to hump your bike, in case I'm not paying full attention at the time.]", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-11 21:02:00", reply_order: 41 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "He laughs. [Okay, sure.]", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-10-11 21:02:00", reply_order: 42 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "[Want a matching outfit or are you more of a hop-on-in-whatever-you're-already-<wbr></wbr>wearing person?  Anyone who's met you would find it plausible that you're courting road rash.]", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-11 21:04:00", reply_order: 43 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "[You know what,] he decides, [I would <em>love</em> a matching outfit.]", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-11 21:09:00", reply_order: 44 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "Bella thinks, and produces one.  Leather won't do the same different-colors-from-different-angles thing, alas, so the jacket has red-fading-pink in its various parts, accented blue, and the pants are blue accented red, similarly.  Dark purple gloves and boots with stitching in both other colors.  It is exactly the right sort of garish.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 21:10:00", reply_order: 45 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "It is <em>awesome</em> is what it is. Alice hugs her impulsively, not that he ever does anything any other way.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-11 21:12:00", reply_order: 46 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "Bella is quite happy to hug him back!  [I'm glad you like 'em.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 21:14:00", reply_order: 47 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "He kisses her forehead, also impulsively, and hugs her some more.<br><br>[I love you. You're the best.]", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-10-11 21:16:00", reply_order: 48 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "[Yes.  Yes I am,] Bella laughs.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 21:17:00", reply_order: 49 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "Alice shuts up and just <em>loves</em> her. Bella is perfect and hugging her is perfect and the things she gives him are perfect and there is nothing he would change about this moment.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-11 21:21:00", reply_order: 50 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "Bella leans into him and into the thought and sighs comfortably.<br><br>[No one's going to walk into the garage and see you hugging the empty air, right?]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 21:34:00", reply_order: 51 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "Alice turns invisible.<br><br>\"Nope.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-11 21:36:00", reply_order: 52 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "Bella snickers softly.  [Good.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 21:37:00", reply_order: 53 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "He giggles right back.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-11 21:39:00", reply_order: 54 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "There ensues a long, silent, invisible hug.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 22:26:00", reply_order: 55 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "It is very snuggly.<br><br>[Oh, hey,] says Alice, as a thought occurs to him. [Mom's throwing a party to, I dunno, celebrate ditching Dad and keeping his money. It's gonna be big and boring and full of boring rich people. Hilary's cooking, though. Wanna come?]", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-11 22:29:00", reply_order: 56 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "[How boring are the rich people?] Bella asks consideringly.  [Like, as far as you know they really aren't that interesting, or, they're some unknown mix of old and new money and maybe some of them run awesome companies but you hold them in general contempt?]", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-11 22:30:00", reply_order: 57 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "[I haven't actually met most of them, but they all know my mom, and she probably met a lot of them through Dad, so there's a good chance they're either boring or assholes. Or boring assholes.]", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-11 22:36:00", reply_order: 58 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "[Is there some non-rude way I could get a copy of the guest list and find everybody online?] Bella asks.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 22:38:00", reply_order: 59 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "[I ask my mom who's coming, she shows it to me, you read my mind?]", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-11 22:40:00", reply_order: 60 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "[That works, yes.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 22:41:00", reply_order: 61 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "[Cool.]<br><br>But he doesn't feel like un-hugging right now.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-10-11 22:41:00", reply_order: 62 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "[No rush.  Unless the party is, like, tomorrow.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 22:42:00", reply_order: 63 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "[Nope! It's in a couple weeks.]", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-10-11 22:46:00", reply_order: 64 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 2, content: "[Cool.]<br><br>And then she decides her speculation about where Janine will imagine they are ought to be true.  Kisses kisses.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-11 22:47:00", reply_order: 65 },
  { post_id: 27, user_id: 3, content: "Mmmmmm, kisses. Alice loves Bella. Her surprises are the best surprises.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-11 22:49:00", reply_order: 66 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "It's approximately ten minutes before someone—not someone interesting, or at least not Googlably so—asks her just <em>who</em> made her dress. The lady in question is dressed very nicely herself, in something sleek and elegant and muted pink-red that complements her curling steel-grey hair.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 00:53:00", reply_order: 0 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "\"Laney did, actually,\" Bella says with a smile.  She has no way to know if this woman is asking her because she likes the dress or because she <em>doesn't</em>, but this answer will cut off most overt sniping.  \"Yours is lovely!\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-12 00:56:00", reply_order: 1 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"Thank you, dear,\" she flutters. \"Judith's son? Why, I had no idea he was so talented!\"<br><br>She likes it, apparently.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 00:58:00", reply_order: 2 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "\"Very much so,\" Bella enthuses merrily.  \"I'm Bella.  What's your name?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 01:00:00", reply_order: 3 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"Sophie,\" says, apparently, Sophie. \"It's just lovely to meet you. Are you one of Laney's friends?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 01:06:00", reply_order: 4 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "\"He's my boyfriend, as of recently,\" Bella says.  \"How do you know the family?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 01:07:00", reply_order: 5 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"Judith and I go way back,\" she says airily. \"I haven't seen much of her since she started seeing that <em>man</em>, but I think that'll change now, don't you?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 01:13:00", reply_order: 6 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "\"Seems likely, especially since you're here,\" Bella says.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 01:13:00", reply_order: 7 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "Sophie chuckles. \"Yes, I suppose so.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 01:18:00", reply_order: 8 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "\"Ooh,\" says Bella, affecting sudden distraction by hors d'oeuvres.  \"I think those might be jalapeno poppers.  It was nice to meet you!\"<br><br>And off she goes towards the poppers and other variously interesting rich people.  [Where are you at?] Bella asks Alice.  [A lady called Sophie just complimented my dress and said you were talented when I told her you made it.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 01:20:00", reply_order: 9 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "[Hiding in the basement,] says Alice. [Sophie, huh? Who's she?]", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-12 01:37:00", reply_order: 10 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "[Random person, unGoogleable, gray hair, pinkish dress, old friend of your mom's who stopped hanging around when your mom started seeing \"that man\".]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 01:38:00", reply_order: 11 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "[Huh. Never heard of her. Maybe I should come up and say hi.]", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-12 01:41:00", reply_order: 12 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "[Quite possibly.]<br><br>Bella finishes her jalapeno popper and turns to the nearest interesting rich person, one of the startup folks.  \"Hi!\" she says.  \"My name is Bella.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 01:43:00", reply_order: 13 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"Hi, Bella!\" says the interesting rich person. \"I'm Nathan.\" Referring to her recently consumed jalapeno popper, \"Are those things any good?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 01:45:00", reply_order: 14 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "\"<em>Everything</em> Hilary makes is good,\" Bella says.  \"This thing in particular is not only good, but also spicy and cheesy.  Nathan... wait, Nathan Hall?\"  She's pretending she doesn't have all publicly available information about him memorized, aww.  \"Didn't you found Postnet?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 01:47:00", reply_order: 15 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"Spicy and cheesy! It's like they were made for me,\" he says, and grabs one.<br><br>\"Yes I did. What's it to you?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 01:51:00", reply_order: 16 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "\"I've heard of it, that's all.  I don't have massive hard drives that need to go anywhere so I haven't used it, but I read an article about it somewhere,\" she says vaguely.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-12 01:52:00", reply_order: 17 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"Well, if you <em>do</em> need to send a massive hard drive somewhere, I know just the people,\" says Nathan with a wink.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 01:53:00", reply_order: 18 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "Bella laughs.  \"Good to know.  Anything else in the works?  I bet you don't personally courier drives, so now that it's up and running they probably don't call you much.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 01:54:00", reply_order: 19 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"Actually, funny story,\" he says, gesturing with his still-untouched popper, \"I did do a run once. It just so happened that we were short a truck, and it just so happened that I was going in the right direction. I dropped off the goods along the way. It was all very exciting.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 02:01:00", reply_order: 20 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "\"Not so exciting that you did it twice, it sounds like,\" Bella points out archly.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-12 02:01:00", reply_order: 21 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"Well, we have people for that.\" He winks again. \"And technically, I'm not qualified.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 02:04:00", reply_order: 22 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "Bella chuckles.  He doesn't seem to want to talk about whatever else he's doing.  That's okay.  There are more people around.  Bella averts her gaze and drifts away after a few seconds have passed in silence and she can do it without being rude.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 02:06:00", reply_order: 23 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "Across the room, Alice has found Sophie and they are getting along, or at least, she's laughing at his jokes.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-12 02:32:00", reply_order: 24 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "Oh, there's a good excuse.  Bella wanders in that direction, touches Alice on the shoulder and smiles - just a gesture of having noticed that he's there - and now she's on the other side of the room, next to Mr. Faceless Corporations.  \"Oh, hello!\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 02:33:00", reply_order: 25 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "Alice grins over his shoulder at her and goes right back to his conversation with the apparently-fascinating Sophie.<br><br>Mr. Faceless Corporations smiles at her. In perhaps an overly friendly way. \"Oh, hello,\" he echoes.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-12 03:08:00", reply_order: 26 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "Bella doesn't like that; shades of Mike in a dude three times Mike's age is about three times less pleasant.  But she is in a room full of people and she has freaking magic; she just won't go off anywhere with this guy, that's all.  [Do you know this one?] she asks Alice, before politely, leaning on that acting pentagon, saying, \"My name's Bella.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 03:11:00", reply_order: 27 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"And I'm Arthur,\" says Faceless Corporations, offering her his hand.<br><br>Alice glances over his shoulder again.<br><br>[One'a Dad's friends,] he says. [Mom really likes his wife.]<br><br>Or neither of them would be here, is the implication.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-12 03:14:00", reply_order: 28 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "Bella shakes.  \"It's nice to meet you.\"<br><br>She likes true things.  Sometimes she likes them so much she won't let other people have any.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-12 03:16:00", reply_order: 29 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"Likewise,\" says Arthur, with a big, big smile. \"What's a nice girl like you doing in a room full of old farts?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 03:18:00", reply_order: 30 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "Bella reaches behind her and grabs Alice's hand, although she doesn't pull on it enough to suggest he turn around.  \"Visiting,\" she says.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-12 03:25:00", reply_order: 31 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"With Junior?\" asks Arthur, raising his eyebrows at their joined hands, as though he can just imagine the sort of person who'd visit Junior. Alice does not, indeed, turn around, nor does he pay Arthur any attention whatsoever, but he does squeeze Bella's hand.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-12 03:27:00", reply_order: 32 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "\"I don't think he really goes by that,\" says Bella, a faint edge to her voice.  She squeezes back and lets go; she communicated her point.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 43, created_at: "2012-10-12 03:29:00", reply_order: 33 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"I can never keep up with these nicknames,\" Arthur says dismissively.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 03:31:00", reply_order: 34 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "\"'Junior' is a nickname,\" Bella points out, shrugging.  \"Ooh, watercress sandwiches.\"  New hors d'oeuvres are being put out periodically, and she's going to be leaning heavily on that.  She strides for the little sandwiches and takes one.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 03:33:00", reply_order: 35 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "Arthur follows, taking one for himself.<br><br>\"Junior's what his family calls him,\" he says. \"Or it was last I checked. See what I mean? I can't keep up.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 03:41:00", reply_order: 36 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "\"Check again,\" Bella recommends.  She turns to a nearby Startup Lady and fakes enthralled surprise.  \"Holy cow, are you Marisa Page?  I <em>just</em> missed your speaking engagement three weeks ago.  Someone from my class on operating systems went, but I had a conflict.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-12 03:43:00", reply_order: 37 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "Marisa smiles. \"Why yes I <em>am</em>!\" she says.<br><br>\"You're a very <em>rude</em> young lady,\" Arthur remarks to Bella.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 03:45:00", reply_order: 38 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "Bella gives Arthur one wide-eyed look of affected hurt, then huffs audibly and takes a step towards Marisa.  She will get mileage out of being a rude <em>young</em> lady if that is what it takes to disengage from him.  \"I got a copy of the handout, though.\"  And looked at it for exactly one second.  \"My classmate wanted to ask you why you're using Common Lisp instead of his favorite implementation, but there wasn't time.  He'll flip if I tell him I met you and got to ask.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 03:47:00", reply_order: 39 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"And what's your classmate's favourite implementation?\" asks Marisa, smiling some more.<br><br>Arthur scowls at both of them and wanders off.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 03:55:00", reply_order: 40 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "\"Scheme,\" Bella replies, bouncing on her toes a little.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 03:57:00", reply_order: 41 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"Well, your classmate might be disappointed with my answer,\" says Marisa, \"but the truth is I'm just more comfortable in Common Lisp.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 04:20:00", reply_order: 42 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "\"I'll tell him,\" Bella says.  \"He might email you.  I think he might have been planning to do that anyway.  I'm all about Python myself.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 04:23:00", reply_order: 43 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"To each her own, I guess,\" says Marisa, with the air of one who definitely does not believe herself.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 04:30:00", reply_order: 44 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "\"Well, I <em>know</em> Lisp, I just get sick of staring at parentheses after a while,\" says Bella.  \"I'm trying to be versatile though.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 04:32:00", reply_order: 45 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"Versatility is good,\" says Marisa. \"Are you in college?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 04:37:00", reply_order: 46 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "\"Freshman at Stanford,\" Bella says.  \"My dad lives here, though, and also there's Laney, so I'm going to be up for the occasional weekend, and a party's a decent excuse for it to be this weekend and not another.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 04:38:00", reply_order: 47 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"Well, come talk to me if you change your mind about parentheses in the next four years, and there might be a job interview in it for you.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 04:41:00", reply_order: 48 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "\"Ooh.  Thanks,\" says Bella, smiling brightly.  \"That's very kind of you!\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-12 04:42:00", reply_order: 49 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"Well, I like helping out my friends,\" she says. \"And my friends' friends. And my friends' sons' friends, apparently.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 04:43:00", reply_order: 50 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "Bella giggles.  \"That doesn't make it any less kind.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 04:44:00", reply_order: 51 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"In that case, thank you,\" she says. \"And you're welcome.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 04:45:00", reply_order: 52 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "Bella grins, and says, \"I don't think I ever told you my name.  I'm Bella Swan.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 04:46:00", reply_order: 53 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"It's nice to meet you, Bella Swan!\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 04:52:00", reply_order: 54 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "\"Likewise.  How do you know Laney's mom, anyway?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 04:53:00", reply_order: 55 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"Knitting,\" says Marisa, \"believe it or not. I met her at a local stitch'n'bitch in New York a few years back. She didn't stick with knitting for long, but she stuck with me.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 04:58:00", reply_order: 56 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "\"Nice,\" Bella says approvingly.  \"My grandmother taught me to knit once, or tried.  Couldn't remember how to cast on after I got home.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 04:58:00", reply_order: 57 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"Try Youtube,\" Marisa advises.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 04:59:00", reply_order: 58 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "\"That would probably help,\" agrees Bella.  \"I really love the internet.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 04:59:00", reply_order: 59 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"Don't we all,\" laughs Marisa.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 05:00:00", reply_order: 60 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "\"Enh, my dad doesn't really understand it,\" Bella volunteers.  \"My mom does though, at least well enough to operate her laptop and email me, and find urban legends to believe.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-12 05:01:00", reply_order: 61 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"Ooh.\" She snickers. \"A crushing indictment of the older generation. But not, I must say, an inaccurate one.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 05:03:00", reply_order: 62 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "\"Plenty of people my age are at least as bad,\" laughs Bella.  \"But the people my age who are terrible with computers don't have tech-savvy children - well, I <em>hope</em> - to mock them.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 05:04:00", reply_order: 63 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"Somewhere in the world, I'm sure there is a teen mother with a five-year-old supergenius patiently telling her to power-cycle the modem again,\" says Marisa.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-12 05:06:00", reply_order: 64 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "Bella chuckles.  \"Probably.  It's a big world.\"<br><br>(And it will be hers, all hers.)<br><br>Eventually Marisa goes to talk to Judith and Bella goes to eat a sausage thing and talk to other Rich People, most of the remaining ones of which are not particularly Interesting and one of whom corners her to talk about his inefficient, ineffective literacy program for children in Portland and how warm-fuzzy it makes him feel for fully twenty minutes.<br><br>Eventually people start to leave.  Bella drifts over to Alice and leans her head on his shoulder.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 43, created_at: "2012-10-12 05:07:00", reply_order: 65 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "\"Hi,\" he says, hugging her. [How'd your getting to know the rich people go?]", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-12 05:38:00", reply_order: 66 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "[I like Marisa, she's cool.  That one guy Arthur is kind of a creep.  The fellow with the literacy program is tiresome.]  \"Hi.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 05:39:00", reply_order: 67 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "[Yeah, Arthur's an asshole,] Alice agrees. [Didn't know he was the kind of asshole who hits on teenagers, but it doesn't surprise me.]", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-12 05:44:00", reply_order: 68 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "[He didn't <em>exactly</em> hit on me.  Then again, Mike never <em>exactly</em> hit on me either,] Bella says disgustedly.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 102, created_at: "2012-10-12 05:45:00", reply_order: 69 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "Alice hugs her some more.<br><br>[The world is full of creepy people,] he says serenely. [Wanna go snuggle somewhere?]", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-10-12 05:48:00", reply_order: 70 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "[Yeah.  I want that.]", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-12 05:49:00", reply_order: 71 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "[Great. Lair?]", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-12 05:52:00", reply_order: 72 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "[I have to leave via motorcycle, since that's how I got here, but if we go into and out of the lair through the basement and make sure we'll notice if someone wanders amongst the columns looking for us, yes.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 05:53:00", reply_order: 73 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "[Works for me,] he says cheerfully, and de-hugs to head for the basement.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-10-12 05:57:00", reply_order: 74 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "They lair in the lair and snuggle.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 05:58:00", reply_order: 75 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "Alice's lair-bed is optimal for snuggling in! It is very soft and well supplied with pillows. Also, conveniently located not three feet away from the door to the basement, so they can see through and check if anyone is looking for them down there.<br><br>It is great and snuggles are great and Bella is great and everything is great.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-12 06:00:00", reply_order: 76 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "Snuggles are indeed great!  Bella needed some snuggles.  That guy bothered her.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 22:30:00", reply_order: 77 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "Then Alice is glad he is helping.<br><br>His mind drifts, predictably, during snuggles; eventually he asks, by brainphone because he is too lazy to lift his face off the pillow, [Can I bake you a cake for your birthday?]", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-12 22:32:00", reply_order: 78 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "[Sure.]  It occurs to Bella that she didn't mention the exact date to him at any point.  [It's the thirteenth.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 22:33:00", reply_order: 79 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "[Okay! Can I <em>bring</em> you the cake?] As opposed to inviting her into his lair for it.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-10-12 22:38:00", reply_order: 80 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "[What's the explanation for how you baked me a cake in Stanford or brought it to Stanford from Forks?]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 22:39:00", reply_order: 81 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "[I'm rich and rich people can do anything? No one will care,] he predicts.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-10-12 22:41:00", reply_order: 82 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "[Mmm... don't think so.  It'd niggle at me if it were someone else.  Either conjure it a cake box that makes it look like you bought it or we can eat in the lair.]", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-12 22:43:00", reply_order: 83 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "[Okay, cake box.]<br><br>Because he can <em>definitely</em> come up with a cake that looks professional by itself.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-12 22:46:00", reply_order: 84 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "That handled, Bella shifts position slightly to take pressure off her elbow.  Snuggle snuggle.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 22:48:00", reply_order: 85 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "Snuggle snuggle!<br><br>Alice happily sets about designing birthday cakes in his head. If he's going to pretend-buy her a cake, it is going to be the most awesome fucking cake she has ever seen.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-12 22:49:00", reply_order: 86 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "[Everyone's going to want to know where it came from.  I think this again calls for \"it was custom from a really exclusive place\",] Bella sighs.  [Put a logo but not a name on the box so it's hard to Google.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 22:50:00", reply_order: 87 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "[I could just make it a plain box,] he suggests. [With your name written on it in Sharpie, so it looks like it was one of a bunch and they needed to label them.]", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-10-12 22:54:00", reply_order: 88 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "[That works too.]", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 22:54:00", reply_order: 89 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "Yay! He did a smart!", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-10-12 22:59:00", reply_order: 90 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 2, content: "Bella laughs and kisses him.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 22:59:00", reply_order: 91 },
  { post_id: 28, user_id: 3, content: "Alice giggles and kisses back.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-12 23:02:00", reply_order: 92 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 3, content: "It turns out that a cake Tegu would have to be insufficiently delicious. So the cake is only <em>inspired</em> by Tegu. It is the black of strong chocolate, with a glossy black chocolate shell in lieu of frosting, and eighteen golden candles chasing one another along its top surface trailing Tegu-like golden streaks. And since the tiered circles design was vetoed, it is rectangular, made in two layers with bright golden frosting between.<br><br>Alice carries it through the door in an enormous plain white cardboard box, reinforced on the bottom with two extra layers of thicker cardboard. Instead of de-invisibling in the stairs, he sneaks all the way outside to visibly come back <em>in</em>side and take the elevator. Helpful strangers push the buttons for him.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-12 23:22:00", reply_order: 0 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 2, content: "Bella grins when she sees him and the cake box.  \"I bet this is going to be the best cake of all time,\" she says.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 23:36:00", reply_order: 1 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 3, content: "\"You are <em>so right</em>,\" says Alice, cheerfully. \"Got somewhere to put it?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-12 23:37:00", reply_order: 2 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 2, content: "Bella moves some books that are on her desk onto her bed, then thinks of a better idea.  \"There's a dorm kitchen.  It's not suitable for actually cooking in, but it has a big table and some plates and stuff.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 23:38:00", reply_order: 3 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 3, content: "\"Good plan!\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-12 23:38:00", reply_order: 4 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 2, content: "And lo they proceed to the kitchen with Bella's cake, and the candles are set alight with the lighter that Alice either remembered to bring or \"remembered to bring\", and they acquire six other dorm residents who lurk around attentively.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 23:42:00", reply_order: 5 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 3, content: "\"Happy birthday,\" says Alice, and kisses her on the cheek. \"Make a wish.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-12 23:44:00", reply_order: 6 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 2, content: "Bella laughs, and decides to actually do that.  She picks the hex-power of variable cognitive speedup that she's been turning over in her head for a while now.  \"Do you think it'll come true?\" she asks Alice in her corniest voice, after blowing out the candles.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-10-12 23:47:00", reply_order: 7 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 3, content: "\"If you wished for delicious cake, then definitely,\" he says, and looks for a knife to cut the cake with.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-12 23:49:00", reply_order: 8 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 2, content: "There is a selection of terrible knives in the kitchen.  A couple of them look like they could successfully go through cake!", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 23:49:00", reply_order: 9 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 3, content: "He grabs the biggest of those, because it is a big cake.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-10-12 23:54:00", reply_order: 10 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 2, content: "Other dorm residents have begun to accumulate (a few initial witnesses went and fetched friends).  Bella knows everyone there, and as long as she gets a nice big corner piece and Alice gets a taste too she is perfectly willing to share.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-12 23:55:00", reply_order: 11 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 3, content: "\"Which part you want?\" he asks, gesturing with the knife to the various available parts of cake anatomy. Corner, edge, middle, lots of candles, no candles...", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-10-12 23:59:00", reply_order: 12 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 2, content: "\"A corner with lots of frosting,\" Bella says.<br><br>Others start putting in their own requests with various amounts of timidity.<br><br>\"I wonder where Janine is,\" Bella says.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-13 00:00:00", reply_order: 13 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 3, content: "\"Okay, hold up,\" says Alice, laughing. \"Birthday girl first.\"<br><br>He cuts Bella her desired slice; it takes a little work to get the knife through the chocolatey shell in some places, but he manages it in the end. Then he moves on to the next nearest person, and so on until everyone in the room has been served, at which point he finally hacks himself off a corner.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-10-13 00:03:00", reply_order: 14 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 2, content: "\"This cake,\" Bella says, \"is the chocolatiest and best cake.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-13 00:08:00", reply_order: 15 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 3, content: "\"Fckn rght,\" Alice mumbles around a mouthful.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-13 00:14:00", reply_order: 16 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 2, content: "Other cake-eaters also seem impressed!", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-13 00:15:00", reply_order: 17 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 3, content: "Janine sidles in and observes the cake from afar.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-10-13 01:01:00", reply_order: 18 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 2, content: "\"Hi, Janine!\" says Bella.  \"Want some of my birthday cake?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-13 01:01:00", reply_order: 19 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yes please!\" says Janine. \"Happy birthday!\"<br><br>\"Comin' right up,\" says Alice. Janine gets a piece with a single guttered candle, which she carefully extracts from its chocolatey surroundings before beginning to eat.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-10-13 01:03:00", reply_order: 20 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 2, content: "\"Thanks!\" says Bella.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-13 01:05:00", reply_order: 21 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 3, content: "\"And thank you for the cake!\" says Janine. \"Where did it come from?\"<br><br>\"I had it made special,\" says Alice.<br><br>\"It is delicious.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-13 01:08:00", reply_order: 22 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 2, content: "\"Death by chocolate,\" remarks Bella, pretending to keel over.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-13 01:09:00", reply_order: 23 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 3, content: "\"Don't drop your cake,\" Alice advises. Janine giggles.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-10-13 01:10:00", reply_order: 24 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 2, content: "Bella's cake is nearly gone anyway.  She polishes it off, thinks, and then cuts herself another sliver.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-13 01:11:00", reply_order: 25 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 3, content: "Alice beams. It is clearly successful cake!", character_id: 19, icon_id: 66, created_at: "2012-10-13 01:11:00", reply_order: 26 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 2, content: "Bella gives him a chocolatey kiss.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-13 01:12:00", reply_order: 27 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 3, content: "He loves her. He loves her a <em>lot</em>.<br><br>He also kisses back very cheerfully and with a complete disregard for their audience.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-13 01:14:00", reply_order: 28 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 2, content: "Bella cuts it out before it descends into unreasonable PDA, though.<br><br>\"What'd you get for your birthday besides cake?\" asks one of the random hall residents.<br><br>\"Besides this lovely cake?  My mom sent me a make-your-own-candle kit and a batch of homemade crackers, and my dad got me some books I wanted,\" Bella says.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-10-13 01:16:00", reply_order: 29 },
  { post_id: 29, user_id: 3, content: "Alice hugs her briefly and then goes to grab himself another piece of cake. Mmm, chocolatey.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-10-13 01:18:00", reply_order: 30 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 3, content: "Perhaps more eye-catching is Delaney, lying stretched out along a bench near one corner of the room and bouncing a basketball off the wall repeatedly with one hand. It rebounds within his reach every time.<br><br>There is also a teacher, standing by the other end of the gym: a tall, broad, muscular woman with long curly black hair. She doesn't seem to be especially busy with anything.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-13 22:13:00", reply_order: 0 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 2, content: "Bella notes Delaney, notes that it would be very easy for him to push her and make it look like it was her fault, and soldiers on nonetheless.  \"Hello, Ms. Finch,\" says Bella.  \"I'm new.  Do you have a minute?  I need to talk to you about accommodations.  I don't have a condition name or anything - my last doctor thought inner ear but couldn't pin anything down; I haven't seen one here yet - but I'm ridiculously clumsy and someone <em>will</em> get hurt, probably me, if I do a majority of gym class activities.\"  She produces her note from her prior teacher and the packet of receipts.  \"You probably get people trying to be excused from things all the time, so I brought these.  If you need to talk to my father about it - or my mother, though that would be a long distance call - you're welcome to.  I can do some things reasonably safely, like most exercise machines and situps; I'm not trying to get out of exercise in general, just injuries.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-13 22:18:00", reply_order: 1 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 3, content: "Delaney ignores both of them. Bounce. Bounce.<br><br>Ms. Finch takes a look at the accumulated evidence, raises her eyebrows, and holds out her hand to accept it.<br><br>\"You must be the Swan kid,\" she says. \"Hi. Nice to meet you... and your medical record.\"<br><br>(Delaney snickers. So he <em>is</em> listening.)", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-13 22:23:00", reply_order: 2 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 2, content: "\"It's only the receipts; you'll have to take my word on what they're for, or call my mom, but at least they substantiate that I'm in and out of the doctor's office regularly,\" says Bella with a tight smile.  \"There's probably some way to get the actual medical record if necessary.  What's on the menu for today?\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-13 22:26:00", reply_order: 3 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 3, content: "\"Volleyball,\" says Ms. Finch, flipping through the receipts. \"Good God.\" (She's reached the broken toes.) \"I wouldn't put you in a volleyball game if you paid me,\" she says as she stacks everything back together and hands it back to Bella. \"You can sit out. Grab a mat and do whatever you can do without breaking any bones in my gym. If I think you're slacking off, I'll let you know.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-13 22:33:00", reply_order: 4 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 2, content: "\"<em>Thank</em> you,\" says Bella warmly, putting away the papers.  She goes and fetches a mat.<br><br>They're right next to where Delaney is bouncing his ball.  Sigh.  She doesn't look directly at him, and he seems pretty good at actually catching the projectile so she's not especially worried about getting clobbered, but she doesn't know what is <em>up</em> with him yet.<br><br>Maybe she'll ask Ms. Finch.  Ms. Finch seems like a sensible person, and has him in one of her classes.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-13 22:37:00", reply_order: 5 }
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 3, content: "Ms. Finch's last words on the subject are a wry, \"You're welcome.\"<br><br>The rhythm of the ball is pretty even - bounce, bounce, bounce. Bounce.<br><br>When Bella approaches, it stops.<br><br>Delaney turns his head to look at her; his jaw and the side of his face are already starting to show bruises from earlier.<br><br>\"Hey,\" he says amicably.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 104, created_at: "2012-09-13 22:42:00", reply_order: 6 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 2, content: "Oh.  Greetings.  Splendid.<br><br>\"Hello.\"  She hauls a mat from where the mats are, and looks for a place that isn't going to be in harm's way when volleyball happens.<br><br>All such places, except for right in front of the door where people are going to start pouring in soon, are also near Delaney.<br><br>Grand.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 102, created_at: "2012-09-13 22:44:00", reply_order: 7 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 3, content: "He observes her looking around.<br><br>\"Do you want me to move?\" he asks, drumming his fingers idly on the basketball, which is now balanced on his chest.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-13 22:47:00", reply_order: 8 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 2, content: "\"I imagine you'll have to do that when you trade your basketball for a volleyball anyway,\" she shrugs.  \"I didn't arrive <em>that</em> early.\"  She spreads out her mat, sits on it, and decides she might as well start stretching.  \"But it's surprisingly observant of you to ask.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 43, created_at: "2012-09-13 22:49:00", reply_order: 9 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 3, content: "\"You say that like I'm gonna play volleyball,\" he says, grinning at some private joke.<br><br>\"You're gonna play volleyball or you're gonna go away,\" Ms. Finch calls from her place near the other end of the room.<br><br>Delaney makes a rude gesture in her direction, still grinning; she doesn't take visible or audible offense, just snorts and goes back to fetching volleyballs from the available supply.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-13 22:53:00", reply_order: 10 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 2, content: "\"Either of those things,\" says Bella.  \"I just hope you don't throw the ball into some jujitsuka's face obviously on purpose and cause him to feed you your own feet before I can summon an ambulance.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-13 22:55:00", reply_order: 11 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 3, content: "<br><br>He laughs.<br><br>\"Now who's surprisingly observant?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-09-13 22:56:00", reply_order: 12 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 2, content: "\"Not really observant.  Only curious.  You do attract attention; people know who you are and were willing to tell me when I tried to figure out how to react.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-13 22:58:00", reply_order: 13 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 3, content: "\"Huh,\" he says, mulling this over.<br><br>\"So why do you care?\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-13 23:01:00", reply_order: 14 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 2, content: "\"Until I made some inquiries, what I saw could have been a bunch of things, and some of those things could have hurt me,\" she says, switching to stretching the other leg.  \"Your... friend... Farber could be a murderer waiting to happen.  I haven't ruled that out - he <em>still</em> would go to prison for a damn long time if he killed you, no matter how many times you shoved him, and you'd still be dead if he did.  You could have some kind of untreated or undertreated mental illness - I haven't ruled that out either, although I don't know what kind it could be.  There could be come complicated hierarchy of violence in the school, which might or might not want to include me, which I'd have to learn about to navigate or safely dismantle.\"  She shrugs.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-13 23:08:00", reply_order: 15 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 3, content: "\"Well, it looks like you got the picture,\" he says serenely. \"I just like getting my ass kicked. Not a problem for you unless you don't like seeing my pretty face all fucked up,\" with a gesture to said face that highlights the bruises and what looks like it might be a knife scar running under the corner of his jaw.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-13 23:12:00", reply_order: 16 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 2, content: "\"I'm not actually sure if masochism is still classified as a mental illness,\" Bella says neutrally.  \"Though if you're going to describe it that way I suppose it could be classified as a bizarre form of cosmetic surgery addiction.  Still, operating via provocation of teenagers with bad impulse control - instead of, I don't know, awaiting the age of majority if you haven't attained it already and then paying a dominatrix - is rather risky.  If you die you don't <em>get</em> to decide whether to press charges, and some kid who's not very bright but could easily have gone his whole life without murdering anyone spends many years in jail.  Do you know how long it's been since there was a murder in Forks?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 43, created_at: "2012-09-13 23:19:00", reply_order: 17 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 3, content: "\"Dominatrix,\" he says with a speculative smile, \"now there's an idea. Nope, not a clue. Do you?\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 106, created_at: "2012-09-13 23:22:00", reply_order: 18 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 2, content: "\"Thirty-seven years.\"  Charlie routinely brags about this.  \"And that one wasn't by <em>or</em> of a resident, it was some people from Port Angeles who were here for some reason.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 43, created_at: "2012-09-13 23:25:00", reply_order: 19 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 3, content: "\"Impressive,\" says Delaney, with apparent sincerity. \"Yeah, I'm from New York. It's probably been, like, a couple hours.\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-13 23:29:00", reply_order: 20 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 2, content: "\"Population density.\"  She shrugs again.  \"But even if you got yourself killed in New York City, someone would go to prison.  If you have a deathwish, I probably can't talk you out of that altogether because I am not a psychologist, but there are ways with less collateral damage.  If you just like getting the crap beaten out of you, there are less hazardous means.\"", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-13 23:32:00", reply_order: 21 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 3, content: "\"Mm, but what if I like getting the crap beaten out of me in front of an <em>audience</em>,\" he says, grinning at her. \"What then?\"", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-13 23:34:00", reply_order: 22 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 2, content: "\"Become a professional wrestler?\" suggests Bella.  \"Pay somebody to pretend they want to kill you in the hallway, and stop at some defined quantity of blood loss?  Hire the dominatrix, set up a video camera, put it on the Internet.\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-13 23:36:00", reply_order: 23 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 3, content: "He laughs.<br><br>\"I'll think about it.\"<br><br>From across the room, Ms. Finch calls, \"Hammond! I want my basketball.\"<br><br>Delaney tosses it in roughly the right direction without looking; it sails through the air, executes a series of diminishing bounces, and finally rolls to a gentle halt against the opposite wall.<br><br>\"Put it <em>away</em>, Hammond, I have better things to do.\"<br><br>He rolls his eyes, but gets up off his bench.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 103, created_at: "2012-09-13 23:41:00", reply_order: 24 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 2, content: "Bella ends her stretch session and starts doing crunches, counting under her breath.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-13 23:43:00", reply_order: 25 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 3, content: "Delaney puts away the basketball and grabs a volleyball from the selection, as Bella predicted. Class proceeds.<br><br>No stray balls threaten Bella's peace on her exercise mat. Ms. Finch glances at her occasionally, but doesn't comment on her exercise routine, so presumably it is unobjectionable.<br><br>When the bell rings, Delaney helps put the balls away and then lingers beside Ms. Finch as the other students stream out of the room. Whatever he's saying, it involves expansive hand gestures. She looks amused.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-13 23:53:00", reply_order: 26 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 2, content: "Bella puts her mat away and looks out the window.  She doesn't really think it will stop raining, but it would sound like something she could think if anyone asks.  If Delaney doesn't leave before this begins to look particularly idiotic, she'll have to give up on talking to Ms. Finch about him until later.", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-14 00:03:00", reply_order: 27 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 3, content: "As the last few students clear out, Ms. Finch looks over at Bella and raises her eyebrows again. Then she cuts Delaney off mid-gesticulation and jerks her thumb at the door. He throws her a mocking salute and leaves.", character_id: 19, created_at: "2012-09-14 00:09:00", reply_order: 28 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 2, content: "Bella trots up to Ms. Finch.  \"First, thanks again for not making me play volleyball.  Second, you seem like you're probably in a position to know more about Delaney than anyone else.  Do you know about the fights he get into?  And why there doesn't seem to have been faculty intervention?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-14 00:10:00", reply_order: 29 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 3, content: "...Ms. Finch sighs.<br><br>\"There is not a lot the faculty can do about that kid,\" she says. \"Between you and me, I wonder why he bothers showing up to school at all. He comes to class when he feels like it, he doesn't show up to detention, and the one time he got suspended, he came to Art anyway and I had to kick him out. Not to mention, it seems kind of backwards to punish a kid for <em>getting</em> beat up, even if he gleefully claims to have started it.\"", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-14 00:21:00", reply_order: 30 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 2, content: "\"He <em>did</em> start the one I saw this morning.  He shoved Dave Farber into a locker.  If someone shoved <em>me</em> into a locker, I'd get a teacher, but the fact that Dave doesn't have very good problem solving skills <em>or</em> a sense of proportion doesn't mean it's swell that he's getting pushed.  If detentions and suspensions don't work, what about his parents?  Don't they do anything?\"", character_id: 31, icon_id: 42, created_at: "2012-09-14 00:24:00", reply_order: 31 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 3, content: "\"I am... not the person to talk to about Hammond's parents,\" says Ms. Finch, looking the least comfortable she has in the short time Bella has known her.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-14 00:27:00", reply_order: 32 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 2, content: "That sounds to Bella like the conversation is over.<br><br>\"Okay.  Thank you anyway,\" Bella says with a polite smile.  \"I'll see you tomorrow.\"<br><br>She'll talk to Charlie about this one.  He knows something about every family in town.", character_id: 31, created_at: "2012-09-14 00:28:00", reply_order: 33 },
  { post_id: 2, user_id: 3, content: "\"See ya,\" the teacher agrees, turning away. Conversation closed.", character_id: 19, icon_id: 65, created_at: "2012-09-14 00:32:00", reply_order: 34 },
  { id: 100752, post_id: 50, user_id: 3, content: "Admiral Naismith's cabin on the <i>Triumph</i> has been stripped of most of his belongings.<br><br>Miles finds this out only <em>after</em> he gets out of the shower, so he's a little irritable by the time he confirms that even his space armour has vanished from its locker. Rather than test the oft-repeated assertion that he could carry on naked and make his officers feel overdressed, however, he gets back into his travel clothes.<br><br>On his way to the briefing room, he passes Sandy Hereld and nods a greeting. She gives him the startled glance of someone who was not expecting her admiral today. \"You're back, sir! That was quick.\"<br><br>Back from what, his two-hour visit to the hospital planetside? \"Eh?\"<br><br>They exchange looks of puzzlement as both continue in opposite directions, Miles toward a lift tube and Hereld toward a cross corridor. He puts the incident out of his mind as he swings into the tube and descends toward his meeting.<br><br>He arrives to find the day's third surprise: more than a dozen officers assembled on time, and Bel Thorne not among them. Bel late to a mission briefing is as likely as an eager child late to its own birthday party. Not to be thought of. Technically it won't be late for another ninety seconds or until Quinn shows up with the files, whichever comes later; still, weird not to see it perched in a chair waiting for presents in the form of a shiny new mission.<br><br>Miles frowns to himself, but shrugs and turns to ask of Elena, \"Did you get a chance to visit your mother?\"", character_id: 27, created_at: "2015-07-23 01:42:00", reply_order: 0 },
  { id: 100753, post_id: 50, user_id: 2, content: "\"I did, yes.  It was... it was nice.  We talked, we hadn't really had a chance before.\"", character_id: 16, created_at: "2015-07-23 01:43:00", reply_order: 1 },
  { id: 100754, post_id: 50, user_id: 3, content: "\"Good,\" he says, smiling, at the news and at the positive effect it seems to have had on Elena's mood.", character_id: 27, created_at: "2015-07-23 01:46:00", reply_order: 2 },
  { id: 100755, post_id: 50, user_id: 2, content: "And in comes Elli, complete with files.  Her possessions not having been mysteriously spirited away, she is in full undress kit.  Files, meet Miles.  She sits.  Miles gets many expectant looks.", character_id: 17, created_at: "2015-07-23 01:47:00", reply_order: 3 },
  { id: 100756, post_id: 50, user_id: 3, content: "He waits for Bel until the actual time of the meeting, and then another half-minute, frowning increasingly.<br><br>\"Is there some reason Captain Thorne is late?\"", character_id: 27, created_at: "2015-07-23 01:48:00", reply_order: 4 },
  { id: 100757, post_id: 50, user_id: 2, content: "The various officers look at each other.  Eventually the eye contact adds up to Elena speaking:<br><br>\"...Was Bel supposed to be back first, Miles?\"", character_id: 16, created_at: "2015-07-23 01:49:00", reply_order: 5 },
  { id: 100758, post_id: 50, user_id: 3, content: "\"Back <em>first</em>? From—?\"<br><br>From whatever extracted Miles's full kit from his cabin? From whatever Lieutenant Hereld expected him to still be out doing? Once is chance, twice is coincidence...<br><br>\"Oh, <em>fuck</em>,\" he says. \"<em>From what?</em>\"", character_id: 27, created_at: "2015-07-23 01:53:00", reply_order: 6 },
  { id: 100759, post_id: 50, user_id: 2, content: "\"...Bel left with you, three days ago, in the Ariel -\"", character_id: 16, created_at: "2015-07-23 01:55:00", reply_order: 7 },
  { id: 100760, post_id: 50, user_id: 2, content: "\"The hell it did,\" hisses Elli.", character_id: 17, created_at: "2015-07-23 01:55:00", reply_order: 8 },
  { id: 100761, post_id: 50, user_id: 3, content: "\"It left with an accurate facsimile, I'm sure,\" says Miles. For fuck's sake, he was sure Mark wouldn't impersonate him - no, he was sure Mark wouldn't impersonate <em>Lord Vorkosigan</em>, and this has proven to be correct, he just failed to consider whether Mark would impersonate Naismith instead. \"Where to?\"", character_id: 27, created_at: "2015-07-23 02:00:00", reply_order: 9 },
  { id: 100762, post_id: 50, user_id: 2, content: "\"Jackson's Whole,\" Elena answers, peering at him minutely.  \"Assuming <em>that</em> was your clone and this is you.\"", character_id: 16, created_at: "2015-07-23 02:03:00", reply_order: 10 },
  { id: 100763, post_id: 50, user_id: 3, content: "\"If you have doubts, get a med scanner. In fact, perhaps I should have made it official policy to scan me every time I show up, because <em>without</em> that policy, my <em>fucking</em> twin brother managed to con Bel Thorne into taking the <em>fucking Ariel</em> to Jackson's <em>fucking</em> Whole!\" He throws up his hands.", character_id: 27, created_at: "2015-07-23 02:10:00", reply_order: 11 },
  { id: 100764, post_id: 50, user_id: 2, content: "\"<em>I'm</em> sure enough this is the real thing, but yes, just for common knowledge,\" says Elli, rolling her eyes.  She nips out, is back a minute later with a scanner, scans him, and passes the device around for all to see.", character_id: 17, created_at: "2015-07-23 02:12:00", reply_order: 12 },
  { id: 100765, post_id: 50, user_id: 3, content: "\"Let it be known,\" says Miles, for the benefit of those who <em>weren't</em> around for that fiasco on Earth, \"that is what a correct and appropriate medical scan of me looks like. I have a twin brother - a trained impersonator, although I was not his intended target - who can fake everything about me except for the old bone fractures. Until just now, he's never actually given it a serious try. And he absconded with the <i>Ariel</i>, of all the ships he could've picked, which means I'm going to have to rethink the upcoming mission if it takes too long to haul him back. This meeting is cancelled.\"", character_id: 27, created_at: "2015-07-23 02:24:00", reply_order: 13 },
  { id: 100766, post_id: 50, user_id: 2, content: "There is some more eye contact, and then some dispersal.", character_id: 17, created_at: "2015-07-23 02:26:00", reply_order: 14 },
  { id: 100767, post_id: 50, user_id: 3, content: "Miles sits at the conference table and puts his head in his hands and swears quietly to himself. He retains enough situational awareness to keep the profanity strictly Betan until everyone who lacks the relevant clearance is out of the room.", character_id: 27, created_at: "2015-07-23 02:28:00", reply_order: 15 },
  { id: 100768, post_id: 50, user_id: 2, content: "Soon even those people are leaving him to it.", character_id: 17, created_at: "2015-07-23 02:30:00", reply_order: 16 },
  { id: 100769, post_id: 50, user_id: 3, content: "The communications turnaround to Jackson's Whole is long enough that a few minutes either way is near-guaranteed to be swallowed up by en-route delays, but any more than that would just be self-indulgent. He drags himself from the table, parks in front of a comconsole, and composes a vid message to Captain Thorne.<br><br>\"Bel,\" he starts off, \"as you may or may not be aware, you've been travelling with the wrong Naismith. I don't know what the two of you think you're doing out there, and I don't care. You are to scan the little shit's bones if you haven't already, and when you verify that he is not me, you are to turn around and make all haste back to Escobar. I will meet you en route. Do not fuck with me on this one. I'm sure Mark's intentions are good, but I will not tolerate impersonation, no matter how well-meaning.\"<br><br>He pauses, considering priorities, then adds: \"If he seems inclined to flee when he hears I'm after him, don't bother trying to chase him down and haul him back to me. The important part here is reuniting you with the fleet. I trust that you find these orders clear and unambiguous.\" And will therefore not deliberately waste time sending back clarification requests until Mark has already grabbed a double fistful of your easily-tugged Betan heartstrings and dragged you into God knows what sort of trouble trying to save all of Jackson's Whole with one commando squad. He trusts this subtext is conveyed by his expression. \"Naismith out.\"<br><br>Then he gets the message sealed and sent, and spends a little while longer poring over the mission files and muttering obscenities. Fucking Mark. This could be anything from misguided heroics to a bizarre and elaborate prank. The one thing he's sure it <em>isn't</em> is a trap. Mark has made it very clear what he thinks of being used as a weapon against Miles. If somebody were to try it against Mark's will, Miles's expectations lie firmly in the area of 'and the body was never found'.<br><br>So.<br><br>He calls up to Nav and Com again, and the comm officer on duty obligingly locates Baz, Elena, and Elli and directs them back to the briefing room. Miles awaits them calmly for about three seconds, and then jumps to his feet and starts pacing.", character_id: 27, created_at: "2015-07-23 02:53:00", reply_order: 17 },
  { id: 100770, post_id: 50, user_id: 2, content: "They come when called, of course.<br><br>\"What's the plan?\" Elli inquires.", character_id: 17, created_at: "2015-07-23 03:44:00", reply_order: 18 },
  { id: 100771, post_id: 50, user_id: 3, content: "He sighs in wry awareness of how stupid the plan is probably going to sound. \"I go after Mark, of course.\"", character_id: 27, created_at: "2015-07-23 03:52:00", reply_order: 19 },
  { id: 100772, post_id: 50, user_id: 2, content: "\"Is this instead of the other contract, or instead of you personally accompanying it, or...?\"", character_id: 17, created_at: "2015-07-23 03:55:00", reply_order: 20 },
  { id: 100773, post_id: 50, user_id: 3, content: "\"No, the other contract has to go forward.\" He shakes his head. \"But we don't need the whole fleet to pull it off. <em>If</em> my recall message reaches Bel, and if nothing else goes wrong along the way, then the <i>Ariel</i> will be back in time for departure and my pursuit will amount to nothing more than a waste of a little fuel. If not, though - Baz, you're in charge of this one.\" <br><br>He brings up a map with a woggle of his pen.<br><br>\"We're smuggling pack-horses, so to speak. Vega Station,\" he indicates the map, \"is an independent deep-space transfer station currently under an arms embargo courtesy of the Cetagandan Empire, who owns one of its neighbours and strong-armed the other two. We come in through Toranira with a perfectly legitimate flight plan filed, headed to Illyrica through Zoave Twilight. And that is exactly where we go, but while we're in Vega space, we drop off three of our ships - not troops or armaments, but the ships themselves. Then at Illyrica we pick up three new ones. Winterfair gifts from Emperor Gregor.\"<br><br>Through the ship's internal system rather than his pen, he sends the specs to Baz's comconsole.<br><br>\"The only trouble is, my brother just walked off with a third of our trade inventory. We were supposed to give away the <i>Triumph</i>, the <i>D-16</i>, and the <i>Ariel</i>. The nearest possible substitute for the missing ship is Truzillo's <i>Jayhawk</i>. I'm <em>really</em> hoping I can reel Thorne back in before we have to leave, because while the replacement ship would be an across-the-board improvement on the <i>Ariel</i>, it falls a little short of the <i>Jayhawk</i>'s firepower. If I take too long chasing down the <i>Ariel</i>, though - Baz, can you talk Captain Truzillo into the trade?\"", character_id: 27, created_at: "2015-07-23 04:19:00", reply_order: 21 },
  { id: 100774, post_id: 50, user_id: 2, content: "Baz peers at the information about the would-be replacement.  \"Oh, wait'll he sees - yes I can.  You could too, of course.\"", created_at: "2015-07-23 04:22:00", reply_order: 22 },
  { id: 100775, post_id: 50, user_id: 3, content: "\"Yeah. But if I'm around to persuade him it will be because Thorne has made it thankfully unnecessary.\"<br><br>He sighs again and sends Baz a data dump of the rest of the mission files.<br><br>\"Elena, I'm taking the <i>Peregrine</i> for this. We wait here for as long as it takes to get the ship ready to go. If we hear back from Bel in the meantime, well and good, we meet it en route and escort the <i>Ariel</i> back to the fleet. If not - the departure schedule for this mission is flexible on the scale of days, but not weeks. I give it until forty-eight hours from this moment. If that time comes and goes and the <i>Ariel</i> is not confirmed on its way to Escobar, Baz, you pack up and head for Vega Station without us.\"", character_id: 27, created_at: "2015-07-23 04:36:00", reply_order: 23 },
  { id: 100776, post_id: 50, user_id: 2, content: "Confirmatory nods all 'round.<br><br>And then: \"Assuming this is more serious than a prank, extracting your clone - especially if he gets all the way to Jackson's Whole - could get dicey, for a definition of dicey meaning 'expensive'...\"", character_id: 17, created_at: "2015-07-23 04:38:00", reply_order: 24 },
  { id: 100777, post_id: 50, user_id: 3, content: "\"ImpSec will cover it.\"", character_id: 27, created_at: "2015-07-23 04:43:00", reply_order: 25 },
  { id: 100778, post_id: 50, user_id: 2, content: "\"Will cover a run after Mark?  What's Mark to them besides a - a leftover from a plot over and done?\"", character_id: 17, created_at: "2015-07-23 04:45:00", reply_order: 26 },
  { id: 100779, post_id: 50, user_id: 3, content: "\"A legitimate potential heir to the Barrayaran Imperium, deserving no less of their attention than I,\" says Miles. \"Which fact I have made more than clear to Simon. If I have to go to expensive lengths to fish him out of whatever shit he's diving into, Simon will cough up the money the same way he would if it were <em>me</em> who needed the rescue.\"", character_id: 27, created_at: "2015-07-23 04:51:00", reply_order: 27 },
  { id: 100780, post_id: 50, user_id: 2, content: "\"A legitimate potential - the entire imperium would go into convulsions,\" Baz says.  \"They wouldn't have <em>you</em> on suspicion of mutation; someone who looks just like you and is a clone to boot can hardly improve on the situation.\"", created_at: "2015-07-23 04:52:00", reply_order: 28 },
  { id: 100781, post_id: 50, user_id: 3, content: "\"I didn't say <em>likely</em>, I said <em>legitimate</em>. But yes, granted, either of us trying for the Imperium would land like a bomb. That doesn't make <em>either</em> of us any less ImpSec's business - more, if anything, against the possibility that someone might try to <em>throw</em> that bomb. It does make me wish Gregor would get married and have five children already, but that's rather outside the scope of my current worries.\"", character_id: 27, created_at: "2015-07-23 04:57:00", reply_order: 29 },
  { id: 100782, post_id: 50, user_id: 2, content: "Baz nods, satisfied with this explanation.  \"Still, best if Bel turns around,\" he sighs.", created_at: "2015-07-23 04:58:00", reply_order: 30 },
  { id: 100783, post_id: 50, user_id: 3, content: "\"Emphatically agreed.\"", character_id: 27, created_at: "2015-07-23 04:59:00", reply_order: 31 },
])

